HP:0004329.label: Abnormal morphology of the posterior segment of the globe

UBERON:0015060.definition: A sphenoid bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.

UBERON:0005904.definition: Any of the ducts that are part of a male reproductive system.
UBERON:0005904.label: duct of male reproductive system

However, muscular dystrophy is used to describe primary myopathies with a genetic basis and a progressive course characterized by progressive skeletal muscle weakness and wasting, defects in muscle proteins, and histological features of muscle fiber degeneration (necrosis) and regeneration. If possible, it is preferred to use other HPO terms to describe the precise phenotypic abnormalities.
HP:0003560.label: Muscular dystrophy

HP:0004328.definition: An abnormality of the anterior segment of the eyeball (which comprises the structures in front of the vitreous humour: the cornea, iris, ciliary body, and lens).
HP:0004328.label: Abnormal anterior segment morphology

UBERON:0019319.definition: An exocrine gland that is part of a integumental system.
UBERON:0019319.label: exocrine gland of integumental system

HP:0011024.definition: An abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract.
HP:0011024.label: Abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract

HP:0004323.definition: An abnormal increase or decrease of weight or an abnormal distribution of mass in the body.
HP:0004323.label: Abnormality of body weight

HP:0004322.definition: A height below that which is expected according to age and gender norms. Although there is no universally accepted definition of short stature, many refer to "short stature" as height more than 2 standard deviations below the mean for age and gender (or below the 3rd percentile for age and gender dependent norms).
HP:0004322.label: Short stature

HP:0003110.definition: An abnormality of the composition of urine or the levels of its components.
HP:0003110.label: Abnormality of urine homeostasis

UBERON:0015152.definition: A gland that is typically found in or near the orbital region, in or around either the medial or lateral canthi, and is typically associated with secretions onto the eyeball or associated ducts. Includes the Harderian, nictitans and lacrimal glands.
UBERON:0015152.label: gland of ocular region

UBERON:0005178.definition: An organ or element that is in the thoracic cavity. Examples: lung, heart, longus colli.
UBERON:0005178.label: thoracic cavity element

UBERON:0036263.definition: The upper part of the larynx, including the epiglottis; the area above the vocal cords.
UBERON:0036263.label: supraglottic part of larynx

UBERON:0010243.definition: An exocrine gland whose secretions are excreted via exocytosis from secretory cells into an epithelial-walled duct or ducts and thence onto a bodily surface or into the lumen; the gland releases its product and no part of the gland is lost or damaged.
UBERON:0010243.label: merocrine gland

HP:0000648.definition: Atrophy of the optic nerve. Optic atrophy results from the death of the retinal ganglion cell axons that comprise the optic nerve and manifesting as a pale optic nerve on fundoscopy.
HP:0000648.label: Optic atrophy

HP:0000726.definition: A loss of global cognitive ability of sufficient amount to interfere with normal social or occupational function. Dementia represents a loss of previously present cognitive abilities, generally in adults, and can affect memory, thinking, language, judgment, and behavior.
HP:0000726.label: Dementia

HP:0100326.definition: Immunological states where the immune system produces harmful responses upon reexposure to sensitising antigens.
HP:0100326.label: Immunologic hypersensitivity

UBERON:0001961.definition: diffuse system of small concentrations of lymphoid tissue found in various sites of the body such as the gastrointestinal tract, thyroid, breast, lung, salivary glands, eye, and skin[WP]. Mucosal-associated lymphoid tissue is typically found as nodules associated with mucosal epithelia with distinct internal structures including B- and T-zones for the activation of lymphocytes[GO].
UBERON:0001961.label: mucosa-associated lymphoid tissue

UBERON:0004785.definition: the mucous membrane lining the respiratory tract
UBERON:0004785.label: respiratory system mucosa

HP:0001336.definition: Very brief, involuntary random muscular contractions occurring at rest, in response to sensory stimuli, or accompanying voluntary movements.
HP:0001336.label: Myoclonus

UBERON:0015212.definition: Any structure that is placed on one side of the left-right axis of a bilaterian.
UBERON:0015212.label: lateral structure

UBERON:0005616.definition: Arteries which arise from the abdominal aorta and distribute to most of the intestines.
UBERON:0005616.label: mesenteric artery

HP:0011675.definition: Any cardiac rhythm other than the normal sinus rhythm. Such a rhythm may be either of sinus or ectopic origin and either regular or irregular. An arrhythmia may be due to a disturbance in impulse formation or conduction or both.
HP:0011675.label: Arrhythmia

UBERON:0005610.definition: Any of the three veins including the common, external and internal iliac veins.
UBERON:0005610.label: iliac vein

UBERON:0004766.definition: A bone that is part of a cranium.
UBERON:0004766.label: cranial bone

HP:0012575.definition: A structural anomaly of the nephron.
HP:0012575.label: Abnormality of the nephron

HP:0003027.definition: Shortening of the middle parts of the limbs (forearm and lower leg) in relation to the upper and terminal segments.

HP:0009122.definition: Absence (due to failure to form) or underdevelopment of bones of the axial skeleton.
HP:0009122.label: Aplasia/hypoplasia affecting bones of the axial skeleton

HP:0025033.definition: A structural anomaly of the digestive system.
HP:0025033.label: Abnormality of digestive system morphology

UBERON:0001893.definition: Part of the forebrain consisting of paired olfactory bulbs and cerebral hemispheres.
UBERON:0001893.label: telencephalon

UBERON:0001820.definition: any of the coil glands of the skin that secrete sweat
UBERON:0001820.label: sweat gland

HP:0001098.definition: Any structural abnormality of the fundus of the eye.
HP:0001098.label: Abnormal fundus morphology

UBERON:0005983.definition: The laminar structure of the heart
UBERON:0005983.label: heart layer

UBERON:0001825.definition: the paired air-filled cavities surrounded by the bones of the face that are lined by mucous membranes and are continuous with the nasal cavity
UBERON:0001825.label: paranasal sinus

UBERON:0002165.definition: The endocardium is an anatomical structure comprised of an endothelium and an extracellular matrix that forms the innermost layer of tissue of the heart, and lines the heart chambers[GO].
UBERON:0002165.label: endocardium

UBERON:0001987.definition: organ of metabolic interchange between fetus and mother, partly of embryonic origin and partly of maternal origin[GO]. The fetal portion of the placenta is known as the villous chorion. The maternal portion is known as the decidua basalis. UBERON:0001987.label: placenta

UBERON:0001829.definition: One of the three largest glands of the oral cavity that secrete most of the saliva, including the parotid, submandibular, and sublingual glands.
UBERON:0001829.label: major salivary gland

UBERON:0001981.definition: A vessel through which blood circulates in the body.
UBERON:0001981.label: blood vessel

HP:0003366.label: Abnormality of the femoral neck or head region

HP:0003367.definition: An abnormality of the femoral neck (which is the process of bone, connecting the femoral head with the femoral shaft).

HP:0003202.definition: The presence of skeletal muscular atrophy (which is also known as amyotrophy).
HP:0003202.label: Skeletal muscle atrophy

UBERON:0013703.definition: Anatomical projection that is part of the integumentl system.
UBERON:0013703.label: integumentary projection

UBERON:0007616.definition: A thin, loose vascular connective tissue that makes up the membranes surrounding joints and the sheaths protecting tendons (particularly flexor tendons in the hands and feet) where they pass over bony prominences. Synovial tissue contains synovial cells, which secrete a viscous liquid called synovial fluid; this liquid contains protein and hyaluronic acid and serves as a lubricant and nutrient for the joint cartilage surfaces[BTO]. Synovial tissue can be found in tendons (tissues that connect muscle to bone), bursae (fluid-filled, cushioning sacs found in spaces between tendons, ligaments, and bones), and the cavity (hollow enclosed area) that separates the bones of a freely movable joint, such as the knee or elbow[BTO].
UBERON:0007616.label: layer of synovial tissue

UBERON:0001711.definition: A fold of skin that covers and protects part of the eyeball. Examples: upper eyelid, lower eyelid, nictitating membrane
UBERON:0001711.label: eyelid

HP:0011793.definition: Neoplasm categorized according to the anatomical site of origin of the neoplasm.
HP:0011793.label: Neoplasm by anatomical site

UBERON:0011591.definition: An axon tract that is part of a diencephalon.
UBERON:0011591.label: tract of diencephalon

HP:0001394.definition: A chronic disorder of the liver in which liver tissue becomes scarred and is partially replaced by regenerative nodules and fibrotic tissue resulting in loss of liver function.
HP:0001394.label: Cirrhosis

HP:0000944.definition: An abnormality of one or more metaphysis, i.e., of the somewhat wider portion of a long bone that is adjacent to the epiphyseal growth plate and grows during childhood.
HP:0000944.label: Abnormality of the metaphysis

HP:0009815.definition: Absence (due to failure to form) or underdevelopment of the extremities.

UBERON:0004085.definition: One of the folds of skin which form the outer lips on both sides of the vaginal opening
UBERON:0004085.label: labium majora

HP:0200000.definition: Different levels of maturation of different bones.
HP:0200000.label: Dysharmonic bone age

UBERON:0001894.definition: The division of the forebrain that develops from the foremost primary cerebral vesicle.
UBERON:0001894.label: diencephalon

HP:0000553.definition: An abnormality of the uvea, the vascular layer of the eyeball.
HP:0000553.label: Abnormality of the uvea

HP:0011015.definition: An abnormality of the concentration of glucose in the blood.
HP:0011015.label: Abnormality of blood glucose concentration

HP:0011017.definition: An abnormality in a cellular process.
HP:0011017.label: Abnormality of cell physiology

HP:0001022.definition: An abnormal reduction in the amount of pigmentation (reduced or absent) of skin, hair and eye (iris and retina).
HP:0001022.label: Albinism

UBERON:0000945.definition: An expanded region of the vertebrate alimentary tract that serves as a food storage compartment and digestive organ. A stomach is lined, in whole or in part by a glandular epithelium.
UBERON:0000945.label: stomach

HP:0011013.definition: An abnormality of the metabolism/homeostasis of a carbohydrate.
HP:0011013.label: Abnormality of carbohydrate metabolism/homeostasis

UBERON:0013631.definition: Ossicle that develops within bands of dense, regular connective tissue (e.g., tendons and ligaments). Sesamoids are generally located proximate to a bony prominence, over which the dense regular connective tissue wraps, and/or a joint or articulation.
UBERON:0013631.label: sesamoid element

HP:0011873.definition: Abnormal number of platelets per volume of blood. In a healthy adult, a normal platelet count is between 150,000 and 450,000 per microliter of blood.
HP:0011873.label: Abnormal platelet count

UBERON:0022303.definition: Single layer of a laminar structure, identified by different density, arrangement or size of cells and processes arranged in flattened layers or lamina[CUMBO].
UBERON:0022303.label: nervous system cell part layer

UBERON:0000916.definition: The subdivision of the vertebrate body between the thorax and pelvis. The ventral part of the abdomen contains the abdominal cavity and visceral organs. The dorsal part includes the abdominal section of the vertebral column.
UBERON:0000916.label: abdomen

UBERON:0002446.definition: A large sesamoid bone found in the distal femur/proximal tibial region of the hindlimb of tetrapods. The patella is the attachment site for proximal hindlimb tendons.[PHENOSCAPE:ad]
UBERON:0002446.label: patella

HP:0000264.definition: An abnormality of the mastoid process, which is the conical prominence projecting from the undersurface of the mastoid portion of the temporal bone.
HP:0000264.label: Abnormality of the mastoid

HP:0002086.definition: An abnormality of the respiratory system, which include the airways, lungs, and the respiratory muscles.
HP:0002086.label: Abnormality of the respiratory system

HP:0001892.definition: An abnormal susceptibility to bleeding, often referred to as a bleeding diathesis. A bleeding diathesis may be related to vascular, platelet and coagulation defects.
HP:0001892.label: Abnormal bleeding

UBERON:0002351.definition: The part of the cardiac conduction system that controls the timing of heart muscle contraction. It relays electrical signals to the AV node[GO]. Subdivision of conducting system of heart at the junction of the right atrium and the superior vena cava, around the sinoatrial nodal branch of right coronary artery and is continuous with the internodal tract[FMA].
UBERON:0002351.label: sinoatrial node

UBERON:0000061.definition: Material anatomical entity that is a single connected structure with inherent 3D shape generated by coordinated expression of the organism's own genome.
UBERON:0000061.label: anatomical structure

HP:0100957.definition: An abnormality of the medulla of the kidney.
HP:0100957.label: Abnormality of the renal medulla

UBERON:0002116.definition: the portion of the small intestine that extends from the jejunum to the colon
UBERON:0002116.label: ileum

HP:0012531.definition: An unpleasant sensory and emotional experience associated with actual or potential tissue damage, or described in terms of such damage.
HP:0012531.label: Pain

UBERON:0002749.definition: A regional part of brain that is part of a cerebellar cortex [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0002749.label: regional part of cerebellar cortex

UBERON:0004756.definition: dermis-derived entity that is made of skeletal tissue.
UBERON:0004756.label: dermal skeletal element

HP:0002164.definition: The presence of developmental dysplasia of the nail.
HP:0002164.label: Nail dysplasia

UBERON:0016490.definition: is the sensory system for the sense of hearing.
UBERON:0016490.label: auditory system

UBERON:0000063.definition: A part of an organ that constitutes a distinct modular sub-unit. In some cases, the organ may also contain other sub-units of identical or similar types, in other cases this may be a distinct entity.
UBERON:0000063.label: organ subunit

UBERON:0001646.definition: Cranial nerve that runs to the eye muscles.
UBERON:0001646.label: abducens nerve

UBERON:0000966.definition: The retina is the innermost layer or coating at the back of the eyeball, which is sensitive to light and in which the optic nerve terminates.
UBERON:0000966.label: retina

UBERON:0000062.definition: Anatomical structure that performs a specific function or group of functions [WP].
UBERON:0000062.label: organ

UBERON:0005103.definition: An epithelium that is part of a mesonephros [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0005103.label: mesonephric epithelium

HP:0002242.definition: An abnormality of the intestine. The closely related term enteropathy is used to refer to any disease of the intestine.
HP:0002242.label: Abnormal intestine morphology

UBERON:0003129.definition: Anatomical structure that is part of the head consisting entirely of cranium and mandible[WP].
UBERON:0003129.label: skull

UBERON:0034925.definition: A collection of anatomical structures that are alike in terms of their morphology or developmental origin.
UBERON:0034925.label: anatomical collection

UBERON:0034923.definition: Material anatomical entity consisting of multiple anatomical structures that are not connected to each other.
UBERON:0034923.label: disconnected anatomical group

UBERON:0002185.definition: the upper conducting airways of the lung; these airways arise from the terminus of the trachea
UBERON:0002185.label: bronchus

UBERON:0002186.definition: the conducting airway of the lungs found terminal to the bronchi; these structures contain neither cartilage nor mucous-secreting glands; the epithelium of the bronchioles becomes thinner with each branching
UBERON:0002186.label: bronchiole

UBERON:0002021.definition: Posterior part of the cerebral hemisphere (MSH)
UBERON:0002021.label: occipital lobe

UBERON:0002020.definition: A nervous system structure composed primarily of nerve cell bodies (somas). May also include dendrites and the initial unmyelinated portion of axons.
UBERON:0002020.label: gray matter

UBERON:0006589.definition: The round ligament of the uterus originates at the uterine horns, in the parametrium. It leaves the pelvis via the deep inguinal ring, passes through the inguinal canal and continues on to the labia majora where its fibers spread and mix with the tissue of the mons pubis[WP]. A fibromuscular band that attaches to the uterus and then passes along the broad ligament, out through the inguinal ring, and into the labium majus[MESH].
UBERON:0006589.label: round ligament of uterus

UBERON:0003126.definition: The trachea is the portion of the airway that attaches to the bronchi as it branches [GO:dph].
UBERON:0003126.label: trachea

HP:0002648.definition: The presence of an abnormal shape of the calvaria (skullcap), that is, of that part of the skull that is made up of the superior portions of the frontal bone, occipital bone, and parietal bones and covers the cranial cavity that contains the brain.
HP:0002648.label: Abnormality of calvarial morphology

HP:0012700.definition: A functional anomaly of the large intestine.
HP:0012700.label: Abnormal large intestine physiology

UBERON:0003457.definition: A bone that is part of a head [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0003457.label: head bone

UBERON:0001621.definition: An artery that supplies the myocardium.
UBERON:0001621.label: coronary artery

UBERON:0001383.definition: A muscle that is part of the region of the hindlimb between the pelvis and ankle.
UBERON:0001383.label: muscle of leg

UBERON:0006059.definition: The falx cerebri, also known as the cerebral falx, so named from its sickle-like form, is a strong, arched fold of dura mater which descends vertically in the longitudinal fissure between the cerebral hemispheres. It is narrow in front, where it is attached to the crista galli of the ethmoid; and broad behind, where it is connected with the upper surface of the tentorium cerebelli. Its upper margin is convex, and attached to the inner surface of the skull in the middle line, as far back as the internal occipital protuberance; it contains the superior sagittal sinus. Its lower margin is free and concave, and contains the inferior sagittal sinus. The falx cerebri is known to calcify with age.
UBERON:0006059.label: falx cerebri

HP:0001249.definition: Subnormal intellectual functioning which originates during the developmental period. Intellectual disability, previously referred to as mental retardation, has been defined as an IQ score below 70.
HP:0001249.label: Intellectual disability

HP:0040126.definition: A deviation from the normal concentration of cobalamin (vitamin B12) in the blood. Vitamin B12 is one of the eight B vitamins.
HP:0040126.label: Abnormal vitamin B12 level

HP:0000163.definition: Abnormality of the oral cavity, i.e., the opening or hollow part of the mouth.
HP:0000163.label: Abnormality of the oral cavity

HP:0005406.definition: Increased susceptibility to bacterial infections of the skin, as manifested by recurrent episodes of infectious dermatitis.
HP:0005406.label: Recurrent bacterial skin infections

UBERON:0001982.definition: Any of the smallest blood vessels connecting arterioles with venules.
UBERON:0001982.label: capillary

HP:0001962.definition: A sensation that the heart is pounding or racing, which is a non-specific sign but may be a manifestation of arrhythmia.
HP:0001962.label: Palpitations

UBERON:0000366.definition: a skeletal muscle whose contraction bends a joint.
UBERON:0000366.label: flexor muscle

HP:0001965.definition: Any anomaly of the scalp, the skin an subcutaneous tissue of the head on which head hair grows.

UBERON:0012275.definition: Epithelium that derives from the mesoderm. [Automatically generated definition].

HP:0011339.definition: An abnormality of the vermilion border, the sharp demarcation between the lip (red colored) and the adjacent normal skin.
HP:0011339.label: Abnormality of upper lip vermillion

HP:0002012.definition: An abnormality of the viscera of the abdomen.
HP:0002012.label: Abnormality of the abdominal organs

HP:0040066.label: Abnormal morphology of bones of the lower limbs

UBERON:0005399.definition: A sex gland that is part of a male reproductive system.
UBERON:0005399.label: male reproductive gland

UBERON:0009201.definition: A nephric duct is a tube that drains a primitive kidney[GO].
UBERON:0009201.label: nephric duct

UBERON:0003693.definition: Anatomical space in the abdominal cavity behind (retro) the peritoneum. It has no specific delineating anatomical structures. Organs are retroperitoneal if they only have peritoneum on their anterior side.
UBERON:0003693.label: retroperitoneal space

UBERON:0003691.definition: The outermost part of the spinal canal. It is the space within the canal (formed by the surrounding vertebrae) lying outside the dura mater.
UBERON:0003691.label: epidural space

UBERON:0001648.definition: Cranial nerve that transmits sound and equilibrium (balance) information from the inner ear to the brain.
UBERON:0001648.label: vestibulocochlear nerve

HP:0000777.definition: Abnormality of the thymus, an organ located in the upper anterior portion of the chest cavity just behind the sternum and whose main function is to provide an environment for T lymphocyte maturation.
HP:0000777.label: Abnormality of the thymus

UBERON:0007375.definition: A multi-tissue structure consisting of bone and soft tissue that forms a part of the roof of the oral cavity. In mammals this is the combination of the primary palate (premaxilla) and the secondary palate. In early tetrapods it consists of the vomer, pterygoid, parasphenoid, palatine and ectopterygoid bones.
UBERON:0007375.label: roof of mouth

UBERON:0007376.definition: The epidermis is the entire outer epithelial layer of an animal, it may be a single layer that produces an extracellular material (e.g. the cuticle of arthropods) or a complex stratified squamous epithelium, as in the case of many vertebrate species[GO].
UBERON:0007376.label: outer epithelium

HP:0012234.definition: Marked decrease in the number of granulocytes.
HP:0012234.label: Agranulocytosis

UBERON:0005409.definition: The part of the digestive system that excludes the hepatobiliary system.
UBERON:0005409.label: alimentary part of gastrointestinal system

UBERON:0010313.definition: An anatomical structure that develops from the neural crest.
UBERON:0010313.label: neural crest-derived structure

UBERON:0011779.definition: A nerve that is part of a head.
UBERON:0011779.label: nerve of head region

UBERON:0035642.definition: Any nerve that innervates the larynx.
UBERON:0035642.label: laryngeal nerve

UBERON:0002113.definition: A paired organ of the urinary tract which has the production of urine as its primary function.
UBERON:0002113.label: kidney

UBERON:0002110.definition: An organ that aids digestion and stores bile produced by the liver[WP].

HP:0000546.definition: A nonspecific term denoting degeneration of the retinal pigment epithelium and/or retinal photoreceptor cells.

HP:0005368.definition: An abnormality of the humoral immune system, which comprises antibodies produced by B cells as well as the complement system.

HP:0004364.definition: The presence of an abnormal concentration of nitrogen compounds.

HP:0003011.definition: Abnormality originating in one or more muscles, i.e., of the set of muscles of body.

UBERON:0003679.definition: The ventral area of the mouth. In organisms with a tongue, this is the area under the ventral surface of the tongue[ncit, modified].

HP:0002209.definition: Decreased number of head hairs per unit area.

UBERON:0001817.definition: The lacrimal glands are paired almond-shaped glands, located in or near the orbital region, that secrete the aqueous layer of the tear film.[WP].

UBERON:0001184.definition: One of two laterally paired arteries that supplies the kidneys. These are large arteries that branch from the dorsal aorta in primitive vertebrates.

HP:0000765.definition: Any abnormality of the thorax (the region of the body formed by the sternum, the thoracic vertebrae and the ribs).

UBERON:0001258.definition: The constricted portion of the urinary bladder, formed by the meeting of its inferolateral surfaces proximal to the opening of the urethra[MP].

HP:0000766.definition: An anomaly of the sternum, also known as the breastbone.

UBERON:0000002.definition: Lower, narrow portion of the uterus where it joins with the top end of the vagina.

HP:0002617.definition: Abnormal outpouching or sac-like dilatation in the wall of an atery, vein or the heart.

HP:0000768.definition: A deformity of the chest caused by overgrowth of the ribs and characterized by protrusion of the sternum.

UBERON:0001257.definition: the smooth triangular region of the wall of the urinary bladder formed by the two ureteral orifices and the internal urethral orifice; it is an area in which the muscle fibers are closely adherent to the mucosa
UBERON:0001257.label: trigone of urinary bladder

HP:0001664.definition: A type of ventricular tachycardia characterized by polymorphioc QRS complexes that change in amplitue and cycle length, and thus have the appearance of oscillating around the baseline in the EKG.

UBERON:0003947.label: brain ventricle/choroid plexus

UBERON:0004277.definition: A muscle that is part of the eye region.

UBERON:0002420.definition: An individual member of a collection of basal ganglia. Basal ganglia are subcortical masses of gray matter in the forebrain and midbrain that are richly interconnected and so viewed as a functional system. The nuclei usually included are the caudate nucleus (caudoputamen in rodents), putamen, globus pallidus, substantia nigra (pars compacta and pars reticulata) and the subthalamic nucleus. Some also include the nucleus accumbens and ventral pallidum[NIF,modified].
UBERON:0002420.label: basal ganglion

UBERON:0009854.definition: Branch or outpocketing of the digestive tract.
UBERON:0009854.label: digestive tract diverticulum

UBERON:0004573.definition: An artery of the systemic circulation, which is the part of the cardiovascular system which carries oxygenated blood away from the heart, to the body, and returns deoxygenated blood back to the heart.
UBERON:0004573.label: systemic artery

HP:0000235.definition: Any abnormality of the fontanelles (the regions covered by a thick membrane that normally ossify in the first two years of life) or the cranial sutures (the fibrous joints in which the articulating bones or cartilages of the skull are connected by sutural ligaments ).
HP:0000235.label: Abnormality of the fontanelles or cranial sutures

HP:0006504.definition: A structural abnormality of a diaphysis of the arm or leg.
HP:0006504.label: Anomaly of the limb diaphyses

UBERON:0007245.definition: Gray matter of the central nervous system which is a collection of clustered nuclei.
UBERON:0007245.label: nuclear complex of neuraxis

HP:0004566.definition: Bulbous appearance of the anterior vertebral bodies, such that the vertebral bodies have the greatest vertical height anteriorly as well as bulbous anterior superior-inferior contours.
HP:0004566.label: Pear-shaped vertebrae

UBERON:0015214.definition: A ligament that is part of a diaphragm.
UBERON:0015214.label: arcuate ligament

HP:0007367.label: Atrophy/Degeneration affecting the central nervous system

UBERON:0004122.definition: Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs concerned with the production and excretion of urine and those concerned with reproduction.
UBERON:0004122.label: genitourinary system

UBERON:0015215.definition: The median arcuate ligament is a ligament under the diaphragm that connects the right and left crura of diaphragm.
UBERON:0015215.label: median arcuate ligament

HP:0011842.definition: An abnormality of the form, structure, or size of the skeletal system.
HP:0011842.label: Abnormality of skeletal morphology

HP:0011843.definition: An abnormality of the function of the skeletal system.
HP:0011843.label: Abnormality of skeletal physiology

HP:0011844.definition: An abnormality of the appendicular skeletal system, consisting of the of the limbs, shoulder and pelvic girdles.
HP:0011844.label: Abnormal appendicular skeleton morphology

UBERON:0002416.definition: Connected anatomical system that forms a barrier between an animal and its environment. In vertebrates, the integumental system consists of the epidermis, dermis plus associated glands and adnexa such as hair and scales. In invertebrates, the integumental system may include cuticle.
UBERON:0002416.label: integumental system

UBERON:0005970.definition: any of the nerve fiber tracts that span the longitudinal fissure between the cerebral and/or cerebellar hemispheres of the brain
UBERON:0005970.label: brain commissure

HP:0006483.definition: The presence of an altered number of of teeth.
HP:0006483.label: Abnormal number of teeth

HP:0011849.definition: Any anomaly in the formation of bone or of a bony substance, or the conversion of fibrous tissue or of cartilage into bone or a bony substance.
HP:0011849.label: Abnormal bone ossification

HP:0006487.definition: A bending or abnormal curvature of a long bone.
HP:0006487.label: Bowing of the long bones

HP:0003241.definition: Underdevelopment of part or all of the external reproductive organs.
HP:0003241.label: External genital hypoplasia

UBERON:0010743.definition: The collection of all meningeal layers that line a central nervous system.
UBERON:0010743.label: meningeal cluster

UBERON:0007651.definition: An anatomical structure that connects two structures
UBERON:0007651.label: anatomical junction

HP:0003125.definition: Reduced activity of coagulation factor VIII. Factor VIII (fVIII) is a cofactor in the intrinsic clotting cascade that is activated to fVIIIa in the presence of minute quantities of thrombin. fVIIIa acts as a receptor, for factors IXa and X.
HP:0003125.label: Reduced factor VIII activity

HP:0000037.definition: Hermaphroditism refers to a discrepancy between the morphology of the gonads and that of the external genitalia. In male pseudohermaphroditism, the genotype is male (XY) and the external genitalia are imcompletely virilized, ambiguous, or complete female. If gonads are present, they are testes.
HP:0000037.label: Male pseudohermaphroditism

HP:0000610.definition: Any structural abnormality of the choroid.
HP:0000610.label: Abnormal choroid morphology

HP:0001596.definition: Loss of hair from the head or body.
HP:0001596.label: Alopecia

UBERON:0017672.definition: A viscus that is part of a abdomen.
UBERON:0017672.label: abdominal viscera

UBERON:0003431.definition: A nerve that is part of a leg [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0003431.label: leg nerve

UBERON:0002203.definition: Vasculature that is part of the eye region.
UBERON:0002203.label: vasculature of eye

UBERON:0002200.definition: Vasculature that is part of a head [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0002200.label: vasculature of head

UBERON:0004983.definition: A mucosa that is part of a vagina [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0004983.label: mucosa of vagina

UBERON:0002204.definition: Anatomical system that consists of the muscular and skeletal systems.
UBERON:0002204.label: musculoskeletal system

UBERON:0000064.definition: A multicellular structure that is a part of an organ.
UBERON:0000064.label: organ part

UBERON:0018260.definition: Any organ component layer that consists of muscle tissue.
UBERON:0018260.label: layer of muscle tissue

UBERON:0014382.definition: A collection of hairs that is part of a craniocervical region.
UBERON:0014382.label: collection of hairs on head or neck

HP:0011442.definition: An anomaly of the control or production of movement in the central nervous system.
HP:0011442.label: Abnormality of central motor function

UBERON:0000060.definition: Organ component adjacent to an organ cavity and which consists of a maximal aggregate of organ component layers.
UBERON:0000060.label: anatomical wall

HP:0002835.definition: Inspiration of a foreign object into the airway.
HP:0002835.label: Aspiration

HP:0009121.definition: An abnormality of the axial skeleton, which comprises the skull, the vertebral column, the ribs and the sternum.
HP:0009121.label: Abnormal axial skeleton morphology

UBERON:0011250.definition: A bone that is part of a autopod region. Note that this incudes the carpal and tarsal bones.
UBERON:0011250.label: autopod bone

HP:0001697.definition: An abnormality of the pericardium, i.e., of the fluid filled sac that surrounds the heart and the proximal ends of the aorta, vena cava, and the pulmonary artery.
HP:0001697.label: Abnormal pericardium morphology

UBERON:0003479.definition: A vein that is part of a thoracic cavity [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0003479.label: thoracic cavity vein

UBERON:0000165.definition: The proximal portion of the digestive tract, containing the oral cavity and bounded by the oral opening. In vertebrates, this extends to the pharynx and includes gums, lips, tongue and parts of the palate. Typically also includes the teeth, except where these occur elsewhere (e.g. pharyngeal jaws) or protrude from the mouth (tusks).
UBERON:0000165.label: mouth

HP:0011297.definition: A morphological abnormality of a digit, i.e., of a finger or toe.
HP:0011297.label: Abnormality of digit

HP:0025032.definition: A functional anomaly of the digestive system.
HP:0025032.label: Abnormality of digestive system physiology

UBERON:0013118.definition: A depression or fissure in the surface of the brain. It surrounds the gyri, creating the characteristic appearance of the brain in humans and other large mammals.
UBERON:0013118.label: sulcus of brain

UBERON:0001774.definition: A skeletal muscle organ that is part of the trunk region.
UBERON:0001774.label: skeletal muscle of trunk

UBERON:0001629.definition: A small epithelioid structure consisting of a small cluster of chemoreceptive and supporting cells located near the bifurcation of the common carotid artery that serves as a chemoreceptive organ that senses the pH, carbon dioxide, and oxygen concentrations in the blood and plays a crucial role in their homeostatic control.
UBERON:0001629.label: carotid body

HP:0008055.definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the uvea, the pigmented middle layer of the eye consisting of the iris and ciliary body together with the choroid.
HP:0008055.label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia affecting the uvea

UBERON:0010001.definition: A small cluster of cells of various types which form a discrete structure, largely delimited by a morphological boundary and whose components work together to make the whole structure capable of a specific function.
UBERON:0010001.label: cell cluster organ

HP:0008053.definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the iris.
HP:0008053.label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the iris

UBERON:0002387.definition: distal portion of the hind limb, including tarsal region, metatarsal region and digits.
UBERON:0002387.label: pes

UBERON:0002384.definition: Tissue with cells that deposit non-polarized extracellular matrix including connective tissue fibers and ground substance.
UBERON:0002384.label: connective tissue

UBERON:0002385.definition: Muscle tissue is a contractile tissue made up of actin and myosin fibers[GO].
UBERON:0002385.label: muscle tissue

UBERON:0004120.definition: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the mesoderm.
UBERON:0004120.label: mesoderm-derived structure

UBERON:0004121.definition: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the ectoderm.
UBERON:0004121.label: ectoderm-derived structure

HP:0002750.definition: A decreased rate of skeletal maturation. Delayed skeletal maturation can be diagnosed on the basis of an estimation of the bone age from radiographs of specific bones in the human body.
HP:0002750.label: Delayed skeletal maturation

UBERON:0000475.definition: Anatomical structure which is a subdivision of a whole organism, consisting of components of multiple anatomical systems, largely surrounded by a contiguous region of integument.
UBERON:0000475.label: organism subdivision

UBERON:0001871.definition: Lower lateral part of the cerebral hemisphere. (MSH)
UBERON:0001871.label: temporal lobe

UBERON:0011141.definition: Ossicle that is part of the appendicular skeleton.
UBERON:0011141.label: appendicular ossicle

HP:0040211.definition: An abnormality of the skin of the palm, that is, the skin of the front of the hand.
HP:0040211.label: Abnormality of the skin of the palm

HP:0003330.definition: Any anomaly in the composite material or the layered arrangement of the bony skeleton.
HP:0003330.label: Abnormal bone structure

UBERON:0013768.definition: Great vessels is a term used to refer collectively to the large vessels that bring blood to and from the heart.
UBERON:0013768.label: great vessel of heart

UBERON:0001182.definition: Mesenteric artery that supplies the whole length of the small intestine except the superior part of the duodenum. It also supplies the cecum and the ascending part of the colon and about half the transverse part of the colon. It arises from the anterior surface of the aorta below the celiac artery at the level of the first lumbar vertebra.
UBERON:0001182.label: superior mesenteric artery

UBERON:0001826.definition: The mucous membrane that lines the nasal cavity[MP].
UBERON:0001826.label: nasal cavity mucosa

HP:0003231.definition: An increased concentration of tyrosine in the blood.
HP:0003231.label: Hypertyrosinemia

UBERON:0003586.definition: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a trunk [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0003586.label: trunk connective tissue

UBERON:0013754.definition: A organ component layer that is part of a integumental system.
UBERON:0013754.label: integumentary system layer

UBERON:0002470.definition: Terminal segment of free limb, immediately distal to the zeugopod region. The fully developed autopod consists of the autopod skeleton plus associated structures such as integument, muscle tissue, vasculature etc. The autopod is divided into mesopodial, metapodiual, and acropodial segments. Examples: human hand, mouse paw, human foot
UBERON:0002470.label: autopod region

UBERON:0001245.definition: Orifice at the opposite end of an animal's digestive tract from the mouth. Its function is to expel feces, unwanted semi-solid matter produced during digestion, which, depending on the type of animal, may be one or more of: matter which the animal cannot digest, such as bones; food material after all the nutrients have been extracted, for example cellulose or lignin; ingested matter which would be toxic if it remained in the digestive tract; and dead or excess gut bacteria and other endosymbionts.
UBERON:0001245.label: anus

UBERON:0002473.definition: A commissure that connects the two cerebral hemispheres. Examples: anterior commissure, corpus callosum.
UBERON:0002473.label: intercerebral commissure

UBERON:0005396.definition: One of: the common carotid artery, or its branches, the external and internal carotid arteries.
UBERON:0005396.label: carotid artery segment

UBERON:0010133.definition: any of the organized aggregations of cells that function as secretory or excretory organs and that release hormones in response to neural stimuli
UBERON:0010133.label: neuroendocrine gland

UBERON:0010039.definition: An organ of the digestive tract that is capable of retaining and storing food
UBERON:0010039.label: food storage organ

HP:0002088.definition: Any structural anomaly of the lung.
HP:0002088.label: Abnormal lung morphology

UBERON:0002372.definition: either of the two small almond-shaped masses of lymph tissue found on either side of the oropharynx
UBERON:0002372.label: tonsil

UBERON:0002371.definition: the soft tissue that fills the cavities of bones
UBERON:0002371.label: bone marrow

UBERON:0002370.definition: Anatomical structure of largely lymphoid tissue that functions in cell-mediated immunity by being the site where T cells develop.
UBERON:0002370.label: thymus

UBERON:0000490.definition: Epithelium which consists of a single layer of epithelial cells. Examples: endothelium, mesothelium, glandular squamous epithelium.[FMA]
UBERON:0000490.label: unilaminar epithelium

UBERON:0006876.definition: A vasculature that is part of a organ.
UBERON:0006876.label: vasculature of organ

UBERON:0015023.definition: A phalanx bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.
UBERON:0015023.label: phalanx endochondral element

UBERON:0015022.definition: A hindlimb bone or its cartilage or pre-cartilage precursor.
UBERON:0015022.label: hindlimb endochondral element

HP:0002683.definition: Abnormality of the calvaria, which is the roof of the skull formed by the frontal bone, parietal bones, and occipital bone.
HP:0002683.label: Abnormality of the calvaria

UBERON:0003221.definition: Endochondral bones that are often elongate and arranged in rows of articulating elements, and form the visible part of the digits.
UBERON:0003221.label: phalanx

UBERON:0002293.definition: A bars of hyaline cartilage located between the distal part of a rib and a costal cartilage, connecting the ribs to the sternum .
UBERON:0002293.label: costochondral joint

HP:0002721.definition: Failure of the immune system to protect the body adequately from infection, due to the absence or insufficiency of some component process or substance.
HP:0002721.label: Immunodeficiency

UBERON:0002279.definition: At the hinder part of the medial wall of the vestibule is the orifice of the vestibular aqueduct, which extends to the posterior surface of the petrous portion of the temporal bone. It transmits a small vein, and contains a tubular prolongation of the membranous labyrinth, the ductus endolymphaticus, which ends in a cul-de-sac between the layers of the dura mater within the cranial cavity. [WP,unvetted].
UBERON:0002279.label: vestibular aqueduct

UBERON:0002037.definition: Part of the metencephalon that lies in the posterior cranial fossa behind the brain stem. It is concerned with the coordination of movement[MESH]. A large dorsally projecting part of the brain concerned especially with the coordination of muscles and the maintenance of bodily equilibrium, situated between the brain stem and the back of the cerebrum , and formed in humans of two lateral lobes and a median lobe[BTO]. Brain structure derived from the anterior hindbrain, and perhaps including posterior midbrain. The cerebellum plays a role in somatic motor function, the control of muscle tone, and balance[ZFA].
UBERON:0002037.label: cerebellum

UBERON:0002553.definition: Anatomical space which contains portions of one or more body substances and is bounded by the internal surface of one maximally connected anatomical structure. Examples: cranial cavity, pharyngeal recess space, nasal cavity, tooth socket, cavity of serous sac, lumen of stomach, lumen of artery, fornix of vagina.
UBERON:0002553.label: anatomical cavity

HP:0000532.definition: An abnormality of the choroid and retina.
HP:0000532.label: Abnormal chorioretinal morphology

UBERON:0004921.definition: A proximal-distal subdivision of the digestive tract.
UBERON:0004921.label: subdivision of digestive tract

UBERON:0004014.definition: One of the folds of skin which form the inner lips on both sides of the vaginal opening
UBERON:0004014.label: labium minora

UBERON:0002495.definition: Long bone is a limb bone that is subcylindrical and has a shaft with periosteum separating the ends of the bones. Long bones are present only in the limbs[VSAO:wd].
UBERON:0002495.label: long bone

UBERON:0001776.definition: vascular layer containing connective tissue, of the eye lying between the retina and the sclera. The choroid provides oxygen and nourishment to the outer layers of the retina. Along with the ciliary body and iris, the choroid forms the uveal tract[WP].
UBERON:0001776.label: optic choroid

UBERON:0006956.definition: The inner lining of the cheeks and lips.
UBERON:0006956.label: buccal mucosa

UBERON:0003258.definition: An endoderm that is part of a foregut [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0003258.label: endoderm of foregut

UBERON:0005057.definition: An organ that is part of a immune system [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0005057.label: immune organ

UBERON:0005055.definition: An organ part that is part of a long bone [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0005055.label: zone of long bone

HP:0009826.definition: Limb shortening because of underdevelopment of one or more bones of the extremities.
HP:0009826.label: Limb undergrowth

UBERON:0000473.definition: A gonad of a male animal. A gonad produces and releases sperm.
UBERON:0000473.label: testis

UBERON:0002486.definition: the vocal apparatus of the larynx, which includes the vocal cords and the opening between them
UBERON:0002486.label: glottis

UBERON:0000471.definition: Multi-tissue structure that is part of a compound organ.
UBERON:0000471.label: compound organ component

UBERON:0000477.definition: Anatomical group that has its parts adjacent to one another.
UBERON:0000477.label: anatomical cluster

UBERON:0000474.definition: The organs and associated structures associated with bearing offspring in a female animal.
UBERON:0000474.label: female reproductive system

UBERON:0034922.definition: A cluster of cells, largely surrounded by a morphological boundary.
UBERON:0034922.label: cell cluster

HP:0012649.definition: A abnormal increase in the inflammatory response to injury or infection.
HP:0012649.label: Increased inflammatory response

UBERON:0000310.definition: The upper ventral region of the torso of an organism.
UBERON:0000310.label: breast

UBERON:0001130.definition: Subdivision of skeletal system that consists of all the vertebra and associated skeletal elements and joints in the body[modified from VSAO].
UBERON:0001130.label: vertebral column

UBERON:0004886.definition: A depression on the surface of the lung where the bronchus, blood vessels and nerves enter.
UBERON:0004886.label: lung hilus

HP:0012647.definition: Any anomaly of the inflammatory response, a response to injury or infection characterized by local vasodilation, extravasation of plasma into intercellular spaces and accumulation of white blood cells and macrophages.
HP:0012647.label: Abnormal inflammatory response

UBERON:0001133.definition: Muscle tissue composed of cardiac muscle cells, forming the muscles of the heart[ZFA,modified].
UBERON:0001133.label: cardiac muscle tissue

HP:0031093.definition: Any anomaly of the structure of the breast.
HP:0031093.label: Abnormal breast morphology

UBERON:0001135.definition: Muscle tissue which is unstriated, composed primarily of smooth muscle fibers surrounded by a reticulum of collagen and elastic fibers. Smooth muscle differs from striated muscle in the much higher actin/myosin ratio, the absence of conspicuous sarcomeres and the ability to contract to a much smaller fraction of its resting length[GO].
UBERON:0001135.label: smooth muscle tissue

UBERON:0002012.definition: An artery that carries deoxygenated blood from heart to the lungs. They are the only arteries (other than umbilical arteries in the fetus) that carry deoxygenated blood..
UBERON:0002012.label: pulmonary artery

UBERON:0010047.definition: Gland of the epithelium lining the oral cavity. The most common are the salivary glands.
UBERON:0010047.label: oral gland

UBERON:0002016.definition: Pulmonary veins are blood vessels that transport blood from the lungs to the heart[GO].
UBERON:0002016.label: pulmonary vein

HP:0000309.definition: An anomaly of the midface, which is a region and not an anatomical term. It extends, superiorly, from the inferior orbital margin to, inferiorly, the level of nasal base. It is formed by the maxilla (upper jaw) and zygoma and cheeks and malar region. Traditionally, the nose and premaxilla are not included in the midface.
HP:0000309.label: Abnormality of the midface

UBERON:0001017.definition: The central nervous system is the core nervous system that serves an integrating and coordinating function. In vertebrates it consists of the neural tube derivatives: the brain and spinal cord. In invertebrates it includes central ganglia plus nerve cord.
UBERON:0001017.label: central nervous system

UBERON:0000304.definition: A layer of membrane around a tendon. It has 2 layers: synovial sheath + fibrous tendon sheath
UBERON:0000304.label: tendon sheath

UBERON:0002019.definition: A cranial nerve that originates from neurons in the medulla and in the cervical spinal cord.
UBERON:0002019.label: accessory XI nerve

UBERON:0002209.definition: Nonsynovial joint in which the articulating bones or cartilages are connected by ligaments. Examples: sagittal suture, inferior tibiofibular syndesmosis, gomphosis.[FMA]
UBERON:0002209.label: fibrous joint

UBERON:0006003.definition: Anatomical structure embedded in or located in the integument that is part of the integumental system. Examples: hair, follicles, skin glands, claws, nails, feathers.
UBERON:0006003.label: integumentary adnexa

UBERON:0034921.definition: An multicellular anatomical structure that has subparts of multiple organs as a part.
UBERON:0034921.label: multi organ part structure

UBERON:0000982.definition: Anatomical cluster that consists of two or more adjacent skeletal structures, which may be interconnected by various types of tissue[VSAO].
UBERON:0000982.label: skeletal joint

UBERON:0000341.definition: In anatomy, the throat is the anterior part of the neck, in front of the vertebral column. It consists of the pharynx and larynx. An important feature of the throat is the epiglottis, a flap which separates the esophagus from the trachea and prevents inhalation of food or drink. The throat contains various blood vessels, various pharyngeal muscles, the trachea (windpipe) and the esophagus. The hyoid bone and the clavicle are the only bones located in the throat of mammals. It is sometimes considered a synonym for fauces. [WP,unvetted].
UBERON:0000341.label: throat

HP:0000152.definition: An abnormality of head and neck.
HP:0000152.label: Abnormality of head or neck

UBERON:0000989.definition: A intromittent organ in certain biologically male organisms. In placental mammals, this also serves as the organ of urination
UBERON:0000989.label: penis

HP:0009797.definition: Cholesteatoma is a benign but potentially destructive growth consisting of keratinizing epithelium located in the middle ear and/or mastoid process. In cholesteatoma, a skin cyst grows into the middle ear and mastoid. The cyst is not cancerous but can erode tissue and cause destruction of the ear.
HP:0009797.label: Cholesteatoma

HP:0000405.definition: An abnormality of vibrational conductance of sound to the inner ear leading to impairment of sensory perception of sound.
HP:0000405.label: Conductive hearing impairment

UBERON:0005911.definition: Epithelium that derives from the endoderm. Examples: urothelium, transitional epithelium of ureter, epithelium of prostatic gland.[FMA]
UBERON:0005911.label: endo-epithelium

HP:0000407.definition: A type of hearing impairment in one or both ears related to an abnormal functionality of the cochlear nerve.
HP:0000407.label: Sensorineural hearing impairment

HP:0001933.definition: This term refers to an abnormally increased susceptibility to bruising (purpura, petechiae, or ecchymoses).
HP:0001933.label: Subcutaneous hemorrhage

HP:0001626.definition: Any abnormality of the cardiovascular system.
HP:0001626.label: Abnormality of the cardiovascular system

HP:0011368.definition: Thickening of the epidermal layer of the skin.
HP:0011368.label: Epidermal thickening

UBERON:0010134.definition: A circumventricular organ that is capable of secreting substances into the cerebrospinal fluid.
UBERON:0010134.label: secretory circumventricular organ

UBERON:0001352.definition: A tube running from the outer ear to the middle ear. The human ear canal extends from the pinna to the eardrum and is about 26 mm in length and 7 mm in diameter.
UBERON:0001352.label: external acoustic meatus

UBERON:0002423.definition: The part of the digestive system that contains the liver and the biliary system
UBERON:0002423.label: hepatobiliary system

UBERON:0001020.definition: Axon tract that crosses the midline of the central nervous system[NIF, modified]. In the context of Drosophila refers to a broad band of axons connecting equivalent neuropils each side of the brain[FBbt].
UBERON:0001020.label: nervous system commissure

UBERON:0014908.definition: Junction between the cerebellum and the pons.
UBERON:0014908.label: cerebellopontine angle

UBERON:0010959.definition: Any muscle organ that is part of either the head or the neck.
UBERON:0010959.label: craniocervical muscle

UBERON:0001821.definition: A holocrine gland that secretes sebum into the hair follicles, or in hairless areas into ducts.[MP].
UBERON:0001821.label: sebaceous gland

HP:0010765.definition: Hyperkeratosis affecting the palm of the hand.
HP:0010765.label: Palmar hyperkeratosis

UBERON:0004535.definition: Anatomical system that has as its parts the heart and blood vessels.
UBERON:0004535.label: cardiovascular system

UBERON:0001775.definition: the thickened portion of the vascular tunic, which lies between the choroid and the iris, composed of ciliary muscle and ciliary processes
UBERON:0001775.label: ciliary body

UBERON:0000977.definition: The invaginated serous membrane that surrounds the lungs (the visceral portion) and lines the walls of the pleural cavity (parietal portion).
UBERON:0000977.label: pleura

UBERON:0005456.definition: The jugular foramen is a large aperture in the base of the skull. It is located behind the carotid canal and is formed in front by the petrous portion of the temporal, and behind by the occipital; it is generally larger on the right than on the left side
UBERON:0005456.label: jugular foramen

UBERON:0001579.definition: Nerve that carries information from the olfactory epithelium to the olfactory bulb[Butler and Hodos].
UBERON:0001579.label: olfactory nerve

UBERON:0008811.definition: An external organ of a male organism that is specialized to deliver sperm during copulation. Intromittent organs are found most often in terrestrial species, as most aquatic species fertilize their eggs externally, although there are exceptions[WP].
UBERON:0008811.label: intromittent organ

HP:0005339.definition: An abnormality of the complement system.
HP:0005339.label: Abnormality of complement system

UBERON:0003704.definition: Passages within the liver for the conveyance of bile. Includes right and left hepatic ducts even though these may join outside the liver to form the common hepatic duct.
UBERON:0003704.label: intrahepatic bile duct

UBERON:0000956.definition: The thin layer of gray matter on the surface of the cerebral hemisphere that develops from the telencephalon. It consists of the neocortex (6 layered cortex or isocortex), the hippocampal formation and the olfactory cortex.
UBERON:0000956.label: cerebral cortex

UBERON:0003703.definition: Passages external to the liver for the conveyance of bile. These include the common bile duct and the common hepatic duct.
UBERON:0003703.label: extrahepatic bile duct

HP:0000083.definition: A reduction in the level of performance of the kidneys in areas of function comprising the concentration of urine, removal of wastes, the maintenance of electrolyte balance, homeostasis of blood pressure, and calcium metabolism.
HP:0000083.label: Renal insufficiency

UBERON:0007329.definition: A duct that collects and carries secretions of the exocrine pancreas to the intestine.
UBERON:0007329.label: pancreatic duct

UBERON:0003442.definition: A nerve that is part of a hindlimb [Automatically generated definition].

It descends through the fibers of the Psoas major, emerging from the muscle at the lower part of its lateral border, and passes down between it and the Iliacus, behind the iliac fascia; it then runs beneath the inguinal ligament, into the thigh, and splits into an anterior and a posterior division. Under the inguinal ligament, it is separated from the femoral artery by a portion of the Psoas major. [WP,unvetted].
UBERON:0001267.label: femoral nerve

UBERON:0010523.definition: A vessel of the microcirculature, lying between the arterioles and venules; includes capillaries (blood and lymphatic), metarterioles and arteriovenous anastomoses.
UBERON:0010523.label: microcirculatory vessel

UBERON:0003831.definition: Any muscle organ that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

HP:0031704.definition: Any functional anomaly of the ear.
HP:0031704.label: Abnormal ear physiology

HP:0031703.definition: Any structural anomaly of the ear.
HP:0031703.label: Abnormal ear morphology

UBERON:0001301.definition: the elongated structure connected to the posterior surface of the testis that transports, stores, and matures spermatozoa between testis and vas deferens
UBERON:0001301.label: epididymis

UBERON:0003834.definition: A blood vessel that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0003834.label: thoracic segment blood vessel

UBERON:0003933.definition: A cartilage element that is part of the cranial skeleton.
UBERON:0003933.label: cranial cartilage

UBERON:0002046.definition: A two-lobed endocrine gland found in all vertebrates, located in front of and on either side of the trachea in humans, and producing various hormones, such as triiodothyronine and calcitonin[BTO].
UBERON:0002046.label: thyroid gland

HP:0011356.definition: An abnormality of the skin that is restricted to a particular body region.

HP:0011357.definition: An abnormality of the density of hair growth.
HP:0011357.label: Abnormality of hair density

HP:0011354.definition: An abnormality of the skin that is not localized to any one particular region.
HP:0011354.label: Generalized abnormality of skin

HP:0011355.definition: A lesion of the skin that is located in a specific region rather than being generalized.
HP:0011355.label: Localized skin lesion

HP:0000277.definition: Any abnormality of the mandible, the bone of the lower jaw.

UBERON:0022275.definition: A sharp bend between consecutive segments of the colon.
UBERON:0022275.label: colic flexure

UBERON:0000946.definition: A membranous fold of the heart that prevents reflux of fluid
UBERON:0000946.label: cardial valve

UBERON:0000947.definition: The main trunk of the systemic arterial system that carries blood from the heart to all the organs and other structures of the body, bringing oxygenated blood to all parts of the body in the systemic circulation
UBERON:0000947.label: aorta

UBERON:0008845.definition: A ligament that does not connect two skeletal elements.

HP:0007370.definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the corpus callosum.

UBERON:0022276.definition: The splenic (or left colic) flexure is a sharp bend between the transverse and the descending colon in the left upper quadrant of humans. The left colic flexure is near the spleen, and hence called the splenic flexure. There are two colic flexures in the transverse colon — the other being the hepatic flexure in the right upper quadrant.
UBERON:0022276.label: splenic flexure of colon

UBERON:0005340.definition: A fiber tracts that connect the dorsal region of the two cerebral hemispheres and span the longitudinal fissure, including the corpus callosum and hippocampal commissure[MP].
UBERON:0005340.label: dorsal telencephalic commissure

UBERON:0000941.definition: Cranial nerve fiber tract which is comprised of retinal ganglion cell axons running posterior medially towards the optic chiasm, at which some of the axons cross the midline and after which the structure is termed the optic tract. Transmits visual information from the retina to the brain[ZFA].
UBERON:0000941.label: cranial nerve II

HP:0012252.definition: A structural anomaly of the respiratory system.
HP:0012252.label: Abnormal respiratory system morphology

UBERON:0002514.definition: Bone tissue forms directly within mesenchyme, and does not replace other tissues[TAO]. Intramembranous ossification is the formation of bone in which osteoblasts secrete a collagen-proteoglycan matrix that binds calcium salts and becomes calcified[GO]. Intramembranous ossification is the way flat bones and the shell of a turtle are formed[GO]. Unlike endochondral ossification, cartilage is not present during intramembranous ossification[WP].
UBERON:0002514.label: intramembranous bone

UBERON:0010230.definition: The core globe-shaped component of the camera-type eye.
UBERON:0010230.label: eyeball of camera-type eye

UBERON:0000948.definition: A myogenic muscular circulatory organ found in the vertebrate cardiovascular system composed of chambers of cardiac muscle. It is the primary circulatory organ.
UBERON:0000948.label: heart

HP:0000050.definition: Underdevelopment of part or all of the male external reproductive organs (which include the penis, the scrotum and the urethra).
HP:0000050.label: Hypoplastic male external genitalia

UBERON:0015833.definition: A epithelium that is part of a foregut.
UBERON:0015833.label: foregut epithelium

HP:0003508.definition: A kind of short stature in which different regions of the body are shortened to a comparable extent.
HP:0003508.label: Proportionate short stature

UBERON:0016435.definition: Subdivision of thorax which includes all structures from the skin to the costal pleura. Examples: There is only one chest wall.

HP:0010919.definition: An abnormality of a homocysteine metabolic process.
HP:0010919.label: Abnormality of homocysteine metabolism

HP:0003133.definition: An abnormality of the spinocerebellar tracts, a set of axonal fibers originating in the spinal cord and terminating in the ipsilateral cerebellum. The spinocerebellar tract convey information to the cerebellum about limb and joint position (proprioception). They comprise the ventral spinocerebellar tract, the anterior spinocerebellar tract, and the posterior spinocerebellar tract.
HP:0003133.label: Abnormality of the spinocerebellar tracts

UBERON:0007702.definition: An axon tract that is part of a brain.
UBERON:0007702.label: tract of brain

UBERON:0001235.definition: the thick outer layer of the adrenal gland that produces and secretes steroid hormones such as corticosterone, estrone and aldosterone
UBERON:0001235.label: adrenal cortex

HP:0000622.definition: Lack of sharpness of vision resulting in the inability to see fine detail.
HP:0000622.label: Blurred vision

UBERON:0000058.definition: A tubular structure that transports secreted or excreted substances.
UBERON:0000058.label: duct

HP:0001051.definition: Seborrheic dermatitis is a form of eczema which is closely related to dandruff. It causes dry or greasy peeling of the scalp, eyebrows, and face, and sometimes trunk.
HP:0001051.label: Seborrheic dermatitis

UBERON:0000017.definition: The part of the pancreas that is part of the exocrine system and which produces and store zymogens of digestive enzymes, such as chymotrypsinogen and trypsinogen in the acinar cells [GO].
UBERON:0000017.label: exocrine pancreas

UBERON:0001585.definition: A vein that carries deoxygenated blood from the upper half of the body into the right atrium of the heart.
UBERON:0001585.label: anterior vena cava

UBERON:0000114.definition: the connective tissue located between the respiratory (airway and alveolar) epithelium, the capillary endothelium and pleural mesothelium; it contains basement membrane composed of collagen, elastin, proteoglycans, and fibronectin
UBERON:0000114.label: lung connective tissue

UBERON:0000117.definition: A tube in the respiratory system. Examples: bronchus, bronchiole, trachea.
UBERON:0000117.label: respiratory tube

UBERON:0016526.definition: Subdivision of telencephalon which is one of a number of subdivisions of each hemisphere separated by both real landmarks (sulci and fissures) and arbitrary boundaries[FMA,modified].
UBERON:0016526.label: lobe of cerebral hemisphere

UBERON:0007914.definition: A bone that is part of a craniocervical region.
UBERON:0007914.label: bone of craniocervical region

UBERON:0000055.definition: A tubular structure that contains, conveys body fluid, such as blood or lymph.

UBERON:0000056.definition: Muscular duct that propels urine from the kidneys to the urinary bladder, or related organs.
UBERON:0000056.label: ureter

HP:0011452.definition: An abnormality of the function of the middle ear.
HP:0011452.label: Functional abnormality of the middle ear

UBERON:0008974.definition: any exocrine gland whose cells bud their secretions off through the plasma membrane producing membrane-bound vesicles in the lumen; the apical portion of the secretory cell of the gland pinches off and enters the lumen; it loses part of its cytoplasm in their secretions; apocrine secretion is functional during hormonal stress or puberty; an example of true apocrine glands are mammary glands, responsible for secreting breast milk.

HP:0010987.definition: An abnormality of the morphology or counts of the cells that make up the immune system.
HP:0010987.label: Abnormality of cellular immune system

HP:0004297.definition: An abnormality of the biliary system.
HP:0004297.label: Abnormality of the biliary system

HP:0004299.definition: The presence of a hernia in the abdominal wall.

HP:0004420.definition: The formation of a blood clot inside an artery.

UBERON:0000959.definition: A decussation of the diencephalon where the fibers of the optic nerve cross

HP:0004354.definition: An abnormality of the metabolism of a carboxylic acid.

HP:0010989.definition: An abnormality of the intrinsic pathway (also known as the contact activation pathway) of the coagulation cascade.

UBERON:0002391.definition: Lymph is the fluid that is formed when interstitial fluid enters the conduits of the lymphatic system through lymph capillaries[WP].

UBERON:0002390.definition: Anatomical system that is involved in the production of hematopoietic cells.
UBERON:0002390.label: hematopoietic system

HP:0002664.definition: An organ or organ-system abnormality that consists of uncontrolled autonomous cell-proliferation which can occur in any part of the body as a benign or malignant neoplasm (tumour).
HP:0002664.label: Neoplasm

HP:0002197.definition: Seizures of with initial involvement of both cerebral hemispheres.
HP:0002197.label: Generalized seizures

UBERON:0002394.definition: Any of the ducts that form the biliary tree, carrying bile from the liver to the small intestine.
UBERON:0002394.label: bile duct

UBERON:0006810.definition: The olecranon is a large, thick, curved bony eminence of the forearm that projects behind the elbow. It is situated at the upper (proximal) end of the ulna, one of the two bones in the forearm. When the hand faces forward the olecranon faces towards the back (posteriorly). It is bent forward at the summit so as to present a prominent lip which is received into the olecranon fossa of the humerus in extension of the forearm. Its base is contracted where it joins the body and the narrowest part of the upper end of the ulna. Its posterior surface, directed backward, is triangular, smooth, subcutaneous, and covered by a bursa. Its superior surface is of quadrilateral form, marked behind by a rough impression for the insertion of the Triceps brachii; and in front, near the margin, by a slight transverse groove for the attachment of part of the posterior ligament of the elbow-joint. Its anterior surface is smooth, concave, and forms the upper part of the semilunar notch. Its borders present continuations of the groove on the margin of the superior surface; they serve for the attachment of ligaments, viz. , the back part of the ulnar collateral ligament medially, and the posterior ligament laterally. From the medial border a part of the Flexor carpi ulnaris arises; while to the lateral border the anconeus muscle is attached.
UBERON:0006810.label: olecranon

UBERON:0015063.definition: A endochondral element that is part of a autopod region.
UBERON:0015063.label: autopod endochondral element

UBERON:0002398.definition: distal segment of the fore limb, including carpal region, metacarpal region and digits.
UBERON:0002398.label: manus

HP:0004348.definition: This term applies to all changes in bone mineral density which (depending on severity) can be seen on x-rays as a change in density and or structure of the bone. Changes may affect all bones of the organism, just certain bones or only parts of bones and include decreased mineralisation as may be seen in osteoporosis or increased mineralisation and or ossification as in osteopetrosis, exostoses or any kind of atopic calicfications of different origin and distribution. The overall amount of mineralization of the bone-organ can be measured as the amount of matter per cubic centimeter of bones, usually measured by densitometry of the lumbar spine or hip. The measurements are usually reported as g/cm3 or as a Z-score (the number of standard deviations above or below the mean for the patient's age and sex). Note that measurement with this method does not reflect local changes in other bones, and as such might not be correct with regard the hole bone-organ.
HP:0004348.label: Abnormality of bone mineral density

UBERON:0001638.definition: Any of the tubular branching vessels that carry blood from the capillaries toward the heart.

Examples: greater omentum, broad ligament of uterus, sigmoid mesocolon.

UBERON:0001733.definition: The muscular, non-bony arch-shaped posterior portion of the palate extending from the posterior edge of the hard palate.

UBERON:0010912.definition: Anatomical cluster consisting of the skeletal elements (i.e. bone elements, cartilage elements, cartilage condensations) that are part of an individual subdivision of the organism. Excludes joints.

UBERON:0001736.definition: Either of the paired compound tubuloalveolar (aka tubuloacinar) major salivary glands composed of both serous and mucous secretory cells and situated beneath the mandible.

UBERON:0001737.definition: A continuation of the pharynx that is involved in breathing, sound production, and protecting the trachea against food aspiration.

UBERON:0001734.definition: Conic projection from the posterior edge of the middle of the soft palate, composed of connective tissue containing a number of racemose glands, and some muscular fibers.

UBERON:0010742.definition: A bone that is part of a pelvic complex. Examples: pubis, ischium, fot phalanx, any tarsal bone, any bone of the pelvic fin or girdle.

UBERON:0003837.definition: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].

UBERON:0008230.definition: Either of two muscles of the calf of the leg.

HP:0000370.label: Abnormality of the middle ear

HP:0002069.definition: Generalized tonic-clonic seizures are generalized seizures with bilateral symmetrical tonic contraction then bilateral clonic contractions of somatic muscles usually associated with autonomic phenomena.
HP:0002069.label: Generalized tonic-clonic seizures

HP:0000240.definition: Any abnormality of the size of the skull.

UBERON:0006925.definition: Any gland that is part of the digestive system.
