HP:0001627.definition: Any structural anomaly of the heart.
HP:0001627.label: Abnormal heart morphology

HP:0000098.definition: A height above that which is expected according to age and gender norms.
HP:0000098.label: Tall stature

UBERON:0004913.definition: A dilation of the duodenal papilla that is the opening of the juncture of the common bile duct and the main pancreatic duct.
UBERON:0004913.label: hepatopancreatic ampulla

UBERON:0005744.definition: Anatomical space that is an opening in a bone, usually for passage of blood vessels or nerves.
UBERON:0005744.label: bone foramen

HP:0010674.definition: The presence of an abnormal curvature of the vertebral column.
HP:0010674.label: Abnormality of the curvature of the vertebral column

HP:0000090.definition: Presence of cysts at the corticomedullary junction of the kidney in combination with tubulointerstitial fibrosis.
HP:0000090.label: Nephronophthisis

HP:0000095.definition: A structural anomaly of the glomerulus.
HP:0000095.label: Abnormality of renal glomerulus morphology

UBERON:0034768.definition: A part of an organism or organ that is continuous with its surroundings and distinguished from its surroundings based on morphology.
UBERON:0034768.label: morphological feature

UBERON:0010147.definition: Any gland, other than the gonad, associated with the genital tract, such as the ampulla of the ductus deferens and the bulbourethral, prostate and vesicular glands of the male.
UBERON:0010147.label: male accessory sex gland

UBERON:0003513.definition: A blood vessel that is part of a trunk [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0003513.label: trunk blood vessel

HP:0012210.definition: Any structural anomaly of the kidney.
HP:0012210.label: Abnormal renal morphology

HP:0012211.definition: An abnormal functionality of the kidney.
HP:0012211.label: Abnormal renal physiology

UBERON:0002135.definition: An atrioventricular valve that is part of the outflow part of the left atrium.
UBERON:0002135.label: mitral valve

UBERON:0010371.definition: Epithelium composed of cells that develops from the ectoderm[FMA,modified].
UBERON:0010371.label: ecto-epithelium

UBERON:0002137.definition: Cardiac valve which has as its parts the anterior, right posterior and left posterior cusps, attached to the fibrous ring of aortic valve.[FMA]
UBERON:0002137.label: aortic valve

UBERON:0004086.definition: one of the system of communicating cavities in the brain that are continuous with the central canal of the spinal cord, that like it are derived from the medullary canal of the embryo, that are lined with an epithelial ependyma, and that contain a serous fluid
UBERON:0004086.label: brain ventricle

HP:0000525.definition: An abnormality of the iris, which is the pigmented muscular tissue between the cornea and the lens, that is perforated by an opening called the pupil.
HP:0000525.label: Abnormality iris morphology

HP:0000668.definition: A developmental anomaly characterized by a reduced number of teeth, whereby up to 6 teeth are missing.
HP:0000668.label: Hypodontia

UBERON:0000065.definition: Anatomical structure that is part of the respiratory system. In mammals consists of upper and lower tracts
UBERON:0000065.label: respiratory tract

HP:0004305.definition: Involuntary contractions of muscle leading to involuntary movements of extremities, neck, trunk, or face.
HP:0004305.label: Involuntary movements

HP:0003468.definition: An abnormality of one or more of the vertebrae.
HP:0003468.label: Abnormal vertebral morphology

UBERON:0003514.definition: A blood vessel that is part of a limb [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0003514.label: limb blood vessel

UBERON:0003516.definition: A blood vessel that is part of a hindlimb [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0003516.label: hindlimb blood vessel

UBERON:0001134.definition: Muscle tissue that consists primarily of skeletal muscle fibers.
UBERON:0001134.label: skeletal muscle tissue

UBERON:0010145.definition: the numerous mucous-secreting glands found in several female mammalian species (including rodents and humans) on the anterior wall of the vagina, around the lower end of the urethra, and possessing a common paraurethral duct which opens (on each side) near the external urethral orifice; they are homologous with the prostate gland in males, have highly variable anatomy, and are believed to be the source of the female ejaculate, a lubricating fluid with a similar consistency to male prostatic fluid that is expelled through the urethra during sexual stimulation; like the male prostate, these glands are susceptible to infection (skenitis), cyst development, and cancer
UBERON:0010145.label: paraurethral gland

UBERON:0003720.definition: The floor of the anterior fossa is formed by the orbital plates of the frontal, the cribriform plate of the ethmoid, and the small wings and front part of the body of the sphenoid; it is limited behind by the posterior borders of the small wings of the sphenoid and by the anterior margin of the chiasmatic groove. The lesser wings of the sphenoid separate the anterior and middle fossae.
UBERON:0003720.label: anterior cranial fossa

HP:0000707.definition: An abnormality of the nervous system.
HP:0000707.label: Abnormality of the nervous system

HP:0001482.definition: Slightly elevated lesions on or in the skin with a diameter of over 5 mm.
HP:0001482.label: Subcutaneous nodule

HP:0001480.definition: The presence of an increased number of freckles, small circular spots on the skin that are darker than the surrounding skin because of deposits of melanin.
HP:0001480.label: Freckling

UBERON:0000014.definition: Any portion of the organ that covers that body and consists of a layer of epidermis and a layer of dermis.
UBERON:0000014.label: zone of skin

UBERON:0001236.definition: the inner portion of the adrenal gland that consists mainly of chromaffin cells which produce, store and secrete neurotransmitters such as epinephrine and norepinephrine
UBERON:0001236.label: adrenal medulla

UBERON:0000016.definition: The part of the pancreas that is part of the endocrine system and is made up of islet cells, which produce insulin, glucagon and somatostatin.
UBERON:0000016.label: endocrine pancreas

HP:0000708.definition: An abnormality of mental functioning including various affective, behavioural, cognitive and perceptual abnormalities.
HP:0000708.label: Behavioral abnormality

HP:0001762.definition: Talipes equinovarus (also called clubfoot) typically has four main components: inversion and adduction of the forefoot; inversion of the heel and hindfoot; equinus (limitation of extension) of the ankle and subtalar joint; and internal rotation of the leg.
HP:0001762.label: Talipes equinovarus

UBERON:0003712.definition: The cavernous sinus (or lateral sellar compartment), within the human head, is a large collection of thin-walled veins creating a cavity bordered by the temporal bone of the skull and the sphenoid bone, lateral to the sella turcica.
UBERON:0003712.label: cavernous sinus

HP:0001760.definition: An abnormality of the skeleton of foot.
HP:0001760.label: Abnormality of the foot

UBERON:0000414.definition: A gland in which the principal secretory cells are mucus secreting cells.
UBERON:0000414.label: mucous gland

HP:0011220.definition: Forward prominence of the entire forehead, due to protrusion of the frontal bone.
HP:0011220.label: Prominent forehead

UBERON:0014892.definition: A muscle organ that consists of skeletal muscle tissue ensheathed in epimysium, that develops from myotome and that is innervated by some somatic motor neuron. Skeletal muscles are typically attached (via a tendon) to a bone but there are exceptions (e.g. intrinsic tongue muscles).
UBERON:0014892.label: skeletal muscle organ

UBERON:0004256.definition: Any muscle organ that is part of a hindlimb zeugopod (lower leg) [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0004256.label: hindlimb zeugopod muscle

HP:0002960.definition: The occurrence of an immune reaction against the organism's own cells or tissues.
HP:0002960.label: Autoimmunity

UBERON:0005881.definition: A subdivision of the autopod that corresponds to one or more bones arranged in series branching from the main limb axis.
UBERON:0005881.label: autopodial extension

UBERON:0003216.definition: Anterior portion of the palate consisting of bone and mucous membranes[GO]. The hard palate is formed from bony processes of the maxilla, premaxilla and palatine[Kardong].
UBERON:0003216.label: hard palate

UBERON:0004885.definition: An anatomical cavity, depression or pit where structures are attached.
UBERON:0004885.label: hilum

HP:0010701.definition: An abnormal deviation from normal levels of immunoglobulins in blood.
HP:0010701.label: Abnormal immunoglobulin level

HP:0010311.definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the breasts.
HP:0010311.label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the breasts

UBERON:0009870.definition: A division of the stomach. The stomach can be divided based on mucosal histology (glandular epithelium and gastric glands) and the relative position and type of gastric gland.
UBERON:0009870.label: zone of stomach

UBERON:0004084.definition: One of the folds of skin which form the inner lips (labia minora) and outer lips (labia majora) on both sides of the vaginal opening.
UBERON:0004084.label: genital labium

UBERON:0003606.definition: A long bone that is part of a limb [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0003606.label: limb long bone

HP:0011389.definition: An abnormality of the function of the inner ear.
HP:0011389.label: Functional abnormality of the inner ear

HP:0006685.definition: The presence of excessive connective tissue in the endocardium.
HP:0006685.label: Endocardial fibrosis

UBERON:0004493.definition: A portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of a myocardium [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0004493.label: cardiac muscle tissue of myocardium

UBERON:0002523.definition: The innermost layer of a blood vessel which is a lining of endothelial cells facing the lumen[Kardong].
UBERON:0002523.label: tunica intima

HP:0030236.definition: Abnormalities of the overall muscle bulk based on clinical observation.
HP:0030236.label: Abnormality of muscle size

UBERON:0002001.definition: Any joint that connects a rib to another structure (or another rib). Examples: costochondral, costovertebral, interchondral, sternocostal joints.
UBERON:0002001.label: joint of rib

UBERON:0004375.definition: A bone that is part of an appendage [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0004375.label: bone of free limb or fin

UBERON:0004376.definition: A bone that is part of a fin [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0004376.label: fin bone

HP:0045058.definition: An anomaly of the size of the testicle (the male gonad).
HP:0045058.label: Abnormality of the testis size

HP:0000969.definition: An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin, or in one or more cavities of the body.
HP:0000969.label: Edema

HP:0000843.definition: Excessive production of parathyroid hormone (PTH) by the parathyroid glands.
HP:0000843.label: Hyperparathyroidism

HP:0100533.definition: Inflammation of the eye, parts of the eye or the periorbital region.
HP:0100533.label: Inflammatory abnormality of the eye

UBERON:0002616.definition: Anatomical divisons of the brain according to one or more criteria, e.g. cytoarchitectural, gross anatomy. Parts may be contiguous in 3D or not, e.g., basal ganglia.
UBERON:0002616.label: regional part of brain

HP:0002493.definition:
A functional anomaly of the upper motor neuron. The upper motor neurons are neurons of the primary motor cortex which project to the brainstem and spinal chord via the corticonuclear, corticobulbar and corticospinal (pyramidal) tracts. They are involved in control of voluntary movements.
Dysfunction leads to weakness, impairment of fine motor movements, spasticity, hyperreflexia and abnormal pyramidal signs.
HP:0002493.label: Upper motor neuron dysfunction

UBERON:0001160.definition: The fundus is the portion of the stomach that lies above the cardiac notch, and contains the fundic glands[GO, Kardong].
UBERON:0001160.label: fundus of stomach

HP:0000962.definition: Hyperkeratosis is thickening of the outer layer of the skin, the stratum corneum, which is composed of large, polyhedral, plate-like envelopes filled with keratin which are the dead cells that have migrated up from the stratum granulosum.
HP:0000962.label: Hyperkeratosis

UBERON:0007798.definition: Anatomical system that consists of all blood and lymph vessels.
UBERON:0007798.label: vascular system

UBERON:0000004.definition: The olfactory organ of vertebrates, consisting of nares, olfactory epithelia and the structures and skeletal framework of the nasal cavity.
UBERON:0000004.label: nose

HP:0000964.definition: Eczema is a form of dermatitis. The term eczema is broadly applied to a range of persistent skin conditions and can be related to a number of underlying conditions. Manifestations of eczema can include dryness and recurring skin rashes with redness, skin edema, itching and dryness, crusting, flaking, blistering, cracking, oozing, or bleeding.
HP:0000964.label: Eczema

UBERON:0000168.definition: A section dividing a colon along a proximal-distal axis.
UBERON:0000168.label: proximal-distal subdivision of colon

UBERON:0007771.definition: A gland that is part of a epidermis.
UBERON:0007771.label: epidermis gland

UBERON:0001810.definition: Anatomical junction where subdivisions of two or more neural trees interconnect with one another to form a network through which nerve fibers of the constituent nerve trees become regrouped; together with other nerve plexuses, nerves and ganglia, it constitutes the peripheral nervous system. Examples: cervical nerve plexus, brachial nerve plexus, sacral nerve plexus[FMA].
UBERON:0001810.label: nerve plexus

UBERON:0004768.definition: Any bone that is part of the lower jaw skeleton. This includes (when present): the dentary/mandible, the articular, the splenial, the suprangular
UBERON:0004768.label: bone of lower jaw

UBERON:0004087.definition: Any of the veins that carries deoxygenated blood from a part of the body into the right atrium of the heart.
UBERON:0004087.label: vena cava

HP:0002797.definition: Osteolysis refers to the destruction of bone through bone resorption with removal or loss of calcium.
HP:0002797.label: Osteolysis

HP:0011035.definition: An abnormality of the cortex of the kidney.
HP:0011035.label: Abnormality of renal cortex morphology

HP:0011032.definition: An abnormality of the regulation of body fluids.
HP:0011032.label: Abnormality of fluid regulation

UBERON:0000167.definition: Anatomical cavity at the start of the digestive tract that that is enclosed by the mouth. The boundaries and contents vary depending on the species. In vertebrates, the boundaries are the oral opening, the cheeks, the palate and (if present) the palatoglossal arch - if this is not present then the mouth and pharynx form the oropharyngeal cavity. The buccal cavity contains the teeth, tongue and palate (when present)
UBERON:0000167.label: oral cavity

HP:0003549.definition: Any abnormality of the soft tissues, including both connective tissue (tendons, ligaments, fascia, fibrous tissues, and fat).
HP:0003549.label: Abnormality of connective tissue

HP:0002813.definition: Any abnormality of bones of the arms or legs.
HP:0002813.label: Abnormality of limb bone morphology

HP:0002812.definition: Coxa vara includes all forms of decrease of the femoral neck shaft angle (the angle between the neck and the shaft of the femur) to less than 120 degrees.
HP:0002812.label: Coxa vara

HP:0002815.definition: An abnormality of the knee joint or surrounding structures.
HP:0002815.label: Abnormality of the knee

HP:0001367.definition: An abnormal structure or form of the joints, i.e., one or more of the articulations where two bones join.
HP:0001367.label: Abnormal joint morphology

HP:0002360.definition: An abnormality of sleep including such phenomena as 1) insomnia/hypersomnia, 2) non-restorative sleep, 3) sleep schedule disorder, 4) excessive daytime somnolence, 5) sleep apnea, and 6) restlessness.
HP:0002360.label: Sleep disturbance

UBERON:0000975.definition: A midventral endochondral skeletal element which represents the origin site of the pectoral muscles[PHENOSCAPE:ad].
UBERON:0000975.label: sternum

HP:0011138.definition: An abnormality of the skin adnexa (skin appendages), which are specialized skin structures located within the dermis and focally within the subcutaneous fatty tissue, comprising three histologically distinct structures: (1) the pilosebaceous unit (hair follicle and sebaceous glands); (2) the eccrine sweat glands; and (3) the apocrine glands.
HP:0011138.label: Abnormality of skin adnexa morphology

UBERON:0010996.definition: A thin layer of cartilage, usually hyaline, on the articular surface of bones in synovial joints.
UBERON:0010996.label: articular cartilage of joint

UBERON:0000974.definition: An organism subdivision that extends from the head to the pectoral girdle, encompassing the cervical vertebral column.
UBERON:0000974.label: neck

HP:0000365.definition: A decreased magnitude of the sensory perception of sound.
HP:0000365.label: Hearing impairment

HP:0000364.definition: An abnormality of the sensory perception of sound.
HP:0000364.label: Hearing abnormality

HP:0002149.definition: An abnormally high level of uric acid in the blood.
HP:0002149.label: Hyperuricemia

UBERON:0014795.definition: Any muscle organ that is part of a pelvic appendage (hindlimb or pelvic fin).
UBERON:0014795.label: pelvic appendage muscle

HP:0100872.definition: An abnormality of the plantar part of foot, that is of the soles of the feet.
HP:0100872.label: Abnormality of the plantar skin of foot

HP:0100871.definition: An abnormality of the palm, that is, of the front of the hand.
HP:0100871.label: Abnormality of the palm

HP:0010917.definition: An abnormality of a tyrosine metabolic process.
HP:0010917.label: Abnormality of tyrosine metabolism

UBERON:0001161.definition: The body of stomach is the part of the stomach that lies between the fundus above and the pyloric antrum below; its boundaries are poorly defined[GO].
UBERON:0001161.label: body of stomach

HP:0003312.label: Abnormal form of the vertebral bodies

UBERON:0001166.definition: the stomach tissue region surrounding and controlling the distal outlet of the stomach, which opens into the duodenum
UBERON:0001166.label: pylorus

UBERON:0001165.definition: the area at the bottom of the stomach on the caudal side of the pyloric canal that contains gastrin-producing G cells, which stimulate acid production, and the luminal pH-sensitive population of somatostatin-producing D cells
UBERON:0001165.label: pyloric antrum

UBERON:0003103.definition: Anatomical structure that has as its parts two or more multi-tissue structures of at least two different types and which through specific morphogenetic processes forms a single distinct structural unit demarcated by bona fide boundaries from other distinct anatomical structures of different types.
UBERON:0003103.label: compound organ

HP:0100543.definition: Abnormality in the process of thought including the ability to process information.
HP:0100543.label: Cognitive impairment

UBERON:0002458.definition: Arteries that supply the spinal cord.
UBERON:0002458.label: spinal artery

UBERON:0001601.definition: Skeletal muscle derived from cranial mesoderm and controls eye movements.
UBERON:0001601.label: extra-ocular muscle

HP:0100547.definition: An abnormality of the forebrain, which has as its parts the telencephalon, diencephalon, lateral ventricles and third ventricle.
HP:0100547.label: Abnormality of forebrain morphology

HP:0001268.definition: Loss of previously present mental abilities, generally in adults.
HP:0001268.label: Mental deterioration

UBERON:0010011.definition: Subcortical masses of gray matter in the forebrain and midbrain that are richly interconnected and so viewed as a functional system. The nuclei usually included are the caudate nucleus (caudoputamen in rodents), putamen, globus pallidus, substantia nigra (pars compacta and pars reticulata) and the subthalamic nucleus. Some also include the nucleus accumbens and ventral pallidum.
UBERON:0010011.label: collection of basal ganglia

UBERON:0001008.definition: The renal system in an anatomical system that maintains fluid balance and contributes to electrolyte balance, acid/base balance, and disposal of nitrogenous waste products..
UBERON:0001008.label: renal system

UBERON:2000364.definition: Laterally flattened haemal spine of an ural vertebra that lacks its arch and supports a few principal caudal lepidotrichia distally. A hypural may articulate or fuse with its ural centrum proximally or may lie ventral to the notochord. A hypural is an unpaired median bone that ossifies perichondrally. (Modified from Monod, 1968 and Arratia and Schultze, 1992).
UBERON:2000364.label: hypural

HP:0001262.definition: A state of abnormally strong desire for sleep during the daytime.
HP:0001262.label: Excessive daytime somnolence

UBERON:0006858.definition: This gland can either be a discrete structure located bilaterally above each kidney, or a cluster of cells in the head kidney that perform the functions of the adrenal gland. In either case, this organ consists of two cells types, aminergic chromaffin cells and steroidogenic cortical cells[GO]
UBERON:0006858.label: adrenal/interrenal gland

HP:0000992.definition: An increased sensitivity of the skin to light. Photosensitivity may result in a rash upon exposure to the sun (which is known as photodermatosis). Photosensitivity can be diagnosed by phototests in which light is shone on small areas of skin.
HP:0000992.label: Cutaneous photosensitivity

UBERON:0001299.definition: the conic expansion of the corpus spongiosum that forms the head of the penis
UBERON:0001299.label: glans penis

UBERON:0004177.definition: Organ that is part of the hematopoietic system.
UBERON:0004177.label: hemopoietic organ

UBERON:0002358.definition: A serous membrane that lines the peritoneal cavity[VHOG,modified].
UBERON:0002358.label: peritoneum

HP:0000999.definition: Any manifestation of a skin disease associated with the production of pus.
HP:0000999.label: Pyoderma

UBERON:0000344.definition: A lining of mostly endodermal origin, covered in epithelium, which is involved in absorption and secretion. They line various body cavities that are exposed to the external environment and internal organs. It is at several places continuous with skin: at the nostrils, the lips, the ears, the genital area, and the anus. The sticky, thick fluid secreted by the mucous membranes and gland is termed mucus. The term mucous membrane refers to where they are found in the body and not every mucous membrane secretes mucus[WP]
UBERON:0000344.label: mucosa

UBERON:0005156.definition: Any anatomical structure that is part of the reproductive system.
UBERON:0005156.label: reproductive structure

UBERON:0002365.definition: A gland that secretes products (excluding hormones and other chemical messengers) into ducts (duct glands) which lead directly into the external environment[WP]. Typical exocrine glands include sweat glands, salivary glands, mammary glands, stomach, liver, pancreas
UBERON:0002365.label: exocrine gland

UBERON:0002544.definition: A subdivision of the autopod that has as part a series of phalanges together with associated vasculature, musculature, integument and nerves. It is continuous with the metapodial subdivision of the autopod, but does not include the metapodials. In species such as humans, fully formed digits are distinct, whereas in other species the digits may be connected by interdigital webbing, or may be completely unseparated (for example, in cetaceans).
UBERON:0002544.label: digit

HP:0000518.definition: A cataract is an opacity or clouding that develops in the crystalline lens of the eye or in its capsule.
HP:0000518.label: Cataract

UBERON:0002453.definition: the evaginations of the mucous membrane of the nasal cavity into the ethmoidal bony labyrinth, forming multiple small paranasal sinuses
UBERON:0002453.label: ethmoid sinus

UBERON:0000021.definition: Anatomical projection that protrudes from the skin. Examples: hair, nail, feather, claw, hoof, horn, wattle, spur, beak, antler, bristle and some scales.
UBERON:0000021.label: cutaneous appendage

UBERON:0012357.definition: A bone that is part of a the digitopodium skeleton - i.e. the acropodial skeleton or the metapodial skeleton.
UBERON:0012357.label: digitopodium bone

UBERON:0004859.definition: A gland that is part of a eye. The eye is a compound unit which depending on the species may consist of an eyeballs plus associated ducts and integumentary structures. Eye glands therefore include the various types of lacrimal gland, the various types of apocrine and sebaceous glands associated with the eyelid.
UBERON:0004859.label: eye gland

HP:0012780.definition: A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of the ear.
HP:0012780.label: Neoplasm of the ear

UBERON:0000411.definition: the part of the cerebral cortex responsible for processing visual information.
UBERON:0000411.label: visual cortex

UBERON:0005172.definition: An organ or element that is in the abdomen. Examples: spleen, intestine, kidney, abdominal mammary gland.
UBERON:0005172.label: abdomen element

UBERON:0005173.definition: An organ or element that is part of the adbominal segment of the organism. This region can be further subdivided into the abdominal cavity and the pelvic region.
UBERON:0005173.label: abdominal segment element

HP:0005832.definition: A type of dysharmonic skeletal maturation in which there is a delay in skeletal maturation whose degree differs markedly in different bones.
HP:0005832.label: Dysharmonic delayed bone age

UBERON:0005177.definition: An organ or element that part of the trunk region. The trunk region can be further subdividied into thoracic (including chest and thoracic cavity) and abdominal (including abdomen and pelbis) regions.
UBERON:0005177.label: trunk region element

HP:0025276.definition: Any functional anomaly of the skin adnexa (skin appendages), which are specialized skin structures located within the dermis and focally within the subcutaneous fatty tissue, comprising three histologically distinct structures: (1) the pilosebaceous unit (hair follicle and sebaceous glands); (2) the eccrine sweat glands; and (3) the apocrine glands.
HP:0025276.label: Abnormality of skin adnexa physiology

UBERON:0005179.definition: An organ or element that is part of the pelvic region. Examples: reproductive organs (in some organisms), urinary bladder, bones of the pelvis.
UBERON:0005179.label: pelvic region element

UBERON:0003074.definition: Paired organ that connects the primitive kidney Wolffian body (or mesonephros) to the cloaca and serves as the anlage for certain male reproductive organs. the Wolffian duct is what remains of the pronephric duct after the atrophy of the pronephros[WP]. In Zebrafish: Duct of the adult kidney (mesonephros), present bilaterally ventral to the somites and leading to the cloacal chamber[ZFA].
UBERON:0003074.label: mesonephric duct

UBERON:0005208.definition: A valve that is part of a right atrium [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0005208.label: right atrium valve

UBERON:0000160.definition: Segment of the alimentary canal extending from the stomach to the anus and, in humans and other mammals, consists of two segments, the small intestine and the large intestine.
UBERON:0000160.label: intestine

UBERON:0005181.definition: An organ that part of the thoracic segment region. This region can be further subdividied chest and thoracic cavity regions.
UBERON:0005181.label: thoracic segment organ

UBERON:0007418.definition: Nerve fibers crossing the midline of the neuraxis relative to their point of origin, on a course to from one level of the nervous system to another. (CUMBO, Heimer, L. The Human Brain, 2nd ed., 1995, pg 6)
UBERON:0007418.label: neural decussation

UBERON:0002072.definition: Lowermost layer of the integumentary system in vertebrates. Types of cells that are found in the hypodermis are fibroblasts, adipose cells, and macrophages. It is derived from the mesoderm, but unlike the dermis, it is not derived from the dermatome region of the mesoderm. The hypodermis is used mainly for fat storage[WP].
UBERON:0002072.label: hypodermis

UBERON:0002075.definition: An organ that is located within the body cavity (or in its extension, in the scrotum); it consists of organ parts that are embryologically derived from endoderm, splanchnic mesoderm or intermediate mesoderm; together with other organs, the viscus constitutes the respiratory, gastrointestinal, urinary, reproductive and immune systems, or is the central organ of the cardiovascular system. Examples: heart, lung, esophagus, kidney, ovary, spleen.
UBERON:0002075.label: viscus

UBERON:0001908.definition: Diencephalic white matter (tract) which is comprised of retinal ganglion cell axons after which they have passed through the optic chiasm[ZFA]. Predominantly white matter structure found in diencephalon consisting of fibers originating in the retina. The optic tract is considered to extend from the point of the optic chiasm and terminates largely, although not exclusively, in the lateral geniculate complex. Other fibers end in the superior colliculus and other structures in the diencephalon, midbrain and brainstem (MM)[NIF].
UBERON:0001908.label: optic tract

HP:0001000.definition: An abnormality of the pigmentation of the skin.
HP:0001000.label: Abnormality of skin pigmentation

UBERON:0036068.definition: The lower portion of the larynx, extending from just beneath the vocal cords down to the top of the trachea.
UBERON:0036068.label: subglottis

UBERON:0005408.definition: Any of any of the secretory or sensory organs located in the brain region around or in relation to the ventricular system that are characterized by extensive vasculature and a lack of a normal blood brain barrier (BBB) and allow for the linkage between the central nervous system and peripheral blood flow.
UBERON:0005408.label: circumventricular organ

HP:0000745.definition: A reduction in goal-directed behavior, that is, motivation, the determinant of behavior and adaptation that allows individuals to get started, be energized to perform a sustained and directed action.
HP:0000745.label: Diminished motivation

HP:0000032.definition: An abnormality of male external genitalia.
HP:0000032.label: Abnormality of male external genitalia

HP:0000035.definition: An anomaly of the testicle (the male gonad).
HP:0000035.label: Abnormality of the testis

UBERON:0000402.label: nasal vestibule

UBERON:0000955.definition: The brain is the center of the nervous system in all vertebrate, and most invertebrate, animals. Some primitive animals such as jellyfish and starfish have a decentralized nervous system without a brain, while sponges lack any nervous system at all. In vertebrates, the brain is located in the head, protected by the skull and close to the primary sensory apparatus of vision, hearing, balance, taste, and smell[WP].

UBERON:0002114.definition: The first part of the small intestine. At the junction of the stomach and the duodenum the alimentary canal is inflected. UBERON:0000483.definition: Portion of tissue, that consists of one or more layers of epithelial cells connected to each other by cell junctions and which is underlain by a basal lamina. UBERON:0000483.label: epithelium

HP:0012718.definition: Abnormal structure of the gastrointestinal tract.

UBERON:0001643.definition: Cranial nerve which connects the midbrain to the extra-ocular and intra-ocular muscles.

HP:0012243.definition: A structural or developmental anomaly of any of the tissues involved in the genital system.

HP:0012369.definition: An abnormality of the malar surface of the zygomatic bone and including the frontal process of maxilla.

HP:0002983.definition: The presence of abnormally small extremities.

UBERON:0013515.definition: A section through the tube or network of tubes that connects the ovaries to the outside of the body.
UBERON:0013515.label: subdivision of oviduct

HP:0002981.definition: An abnormality of the calf, i.e. of the posterior part of the lower leg.
HP:0002981.label: Abnormality of the calf

HP:0003510.definition: A severe degree of short stature, more than -4 SD from the mean corrected for age and sex.
HP:0003510.label: Severe short stature

UBERON:0005388.definition: An array of photoreceptors and any supporting cells found in an eye.
UBERON:0005388.label: photoreceptor array

UBERON:0010314.definition: An anatomical structure that has some part that develops from the neural crest.
UBERON:0010314.label: structure with developmental contribution from neural crest

UBERON:0000059.definition: A subdivision of the digestive tract that connects the small intestine to the cloaca or anus. Lacks or has few villi[Kardong].
UBERON:0000059.label: large intestine

UBERON:0000083.definition: A mesonephric tubule is an epithelial tube that is part of the mesonephros[GO]. Genital ridge that is next to the mesonephros[WP].
UBERON:0000083.label: mesonephric tubule

HP:0004337.definition: Abnormality of an amino acid metabolic process.
HP:0004337.label: Abnormality of amino acid metabolism

HP:0000927.definition: The bones of the skeleton undergo a series of characteristic changes in size, shape, and calcification from fetal life until puberty. An abnormality of this process can include delayed or accelerated skeletal maturation, or deviation of some, but not all bones from the expected patterns of maturation.
HP:0000927.label: Abnormality of skeletal maturation

HP:0000926.definition: A flattened vertebral body shape with reduced distance between the vertebral endplates.
HP:0000926.label: Platyspondyly

HP:0000925.definition: Any abnormality of the vertebral column.
HP:0000925.label: Abnormality of the vertebral column

UBERON:0036215.definition: Material anatomical entity that forms the outermost boundary of an anatomical structure.

UBERON:0007100.definition: A hollow, muscular organ, which, by contracting rhythmically, keeps up the circulation of the blood or analogs[GO,modified].
UBERON:0007100.label: primary circulatory organ

UBERON:0007842.definition: Bone element that arises as a result of intramembranous ossification.
UBERON:0007842.label: membrane bone

UBERON:0000045.definition: A biological tissue mass, most commonly a mass of nerve cell bodies.
UBERON:0000045.label: ganglion

UBERON:0000042.definition: multi-tissue structure that is comprised of a secretory epithelial layer (mesothelium) and a connective tissue layer.
UBERON:0000042.label: serous membrane

HP:0010993.definition: An abnormality of the cerebral subcortex.
HP:0010993.label: Abnormality of the cerebral subcortex

UBERON:0010009.definition: A regional part of brain consisting of multiple brain regions that are not related through a simple volummetric part of hierarchy, e.g., basal ganglia[NIF].
UBERON:0010009.label: aggregate regional part of brain

UBERON:0006052.definition: A digit that is part of a digit 5 plus metapodial segment.
UBERON:0006052.label: digit 5

HP:0010995.definition: An abnormality of dicarboxylic acid metabolism.
HP:0010995.label: Abnormality of dicarboxylic acid metabolism

UBERON:0005358.definition: A layer in the central nervous system that lines system of communicating cavities in the brain and spinal cord.

UBERON:0016525.definition: Frontal lobe is the anterior-most of five lobes of the cerebral hemisphere. It is bounded by the central sulcus on its posterior border and by the longitudinal cerebral fissure on its medial border.

HP:0004431.definition: An immunodeficiency defined by the absent or suboptimal functioning of one of the complement system proteins.

HP:0004430.definition: A combined immunodeficiency primary immune deficiency that is characterized by a more severe defect in both the T- and B-lymphocyte systems.
HP:0004430.label: Severe combined immunodeficiency

UBERON:0005352.definition: The cord-like structure in males comprising the vas deferens and associated tissue that runs from the abdomen down to each testis[MP].
UBERON:0005352.label: spermatic cord

HP:0009115.definition: Absence (due to failure to form) or underdevelopment of one or more components of the skeleton.
HP:0009115.label: Aplasia/hypoplasia involving the skeleton

UBERON:0003498.definition: A blood vessel that is part of a heart [Automatically generated definition].

HP:0009116.label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia involving bones of the skull

UBERON:0001872.definition: Upper central part of the cerebral hemisphere. (MSH)
UBERON:0001872.label: parietal lobe

UBERON:0001994.definition: Cartilage tissue primarily composed of type II collagen (thin fibrils) and a glassy appearance.

UBERON:0003570.definition: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0003570.label: respiratory system connective tissue

HP:0003355.definition: An increased concentration of an amino acid in the urine.
HP:0003355.label: Aminoaciduria

HP:0000819.definition: A group of abnormalities characterized by hyperglycemia and glucose intolerance.
HP:0000819.label: Diabetes mellitus

HP:0000818.definition: An abnormality of the endocrine system.
HP:0000818.label: Abnormality of the endocrine system

UBERON:0001361.definition: In the human body, the femoral vein is a blood vessel that accompanies the femoral artery in the femoral sheath. It begins at the adductor canal (also known as Hunter's canal) and is a continuation of the popliteal vein. It ends at the inferior margin of the inguinal ligament, where it becomes the external iliac vein. [WP,unvetted].
UBERON:0001361.label: femoral vein

UBERON:0001645.definition: Cranial nerve that has three branches - the ophthalmic (supplying the skin of the nose and upper jaw), the maxillary and the mandibular (supplying the lower jaw).
UBERON:0001645.label: trigeminal nerve

HP:0100508.definition: An anomaly in the metabolism of a vitamin.
HP:0100508.label: Abnormality of vitamin metabolism

UBERON:0000057.definition: the fibromuscular tubular canal through which urine is discharged from the bladder to the exterior via the external urinary meatus; in males, the urethra is joined by the ejaculatory ducts and serves as a passageway for semen during ejaculation, as well as a canal for urine during voiding; in females, the urethra is shorter and emerges above the vaginal opening
UBERON:0000057.label: urethra

UBERON:0011826.definition: Lobular organ the parenchyma of which consists of glandular acini which communicate with the vestibule of vagina. Examples: right vestibular gland, lesser vestibular gland.
UBERON:0011826.label: vestibular gland

UBERON:0022277.definition: Hepatic (or the right colic) flexure is the sharp bend between the ascending and the transverse colon. The right colic flexure is adjacent to the liver, and is therefore also known as the hepatic flexure. Thus, the left colic flexure is also known as the splenic flexure (as it is close to the spleen). The hepatic flexure lies in the right upper quadrant of the abdomen in humans.
UBERON:0022277.label: hepatic flexure of colon

UBERON:0001723.definition: A muscular organ in the floor of the mouth.
UBERON:0001723.label: tongue

UBERON:0001724.definition: One of the paired paranasal sinuses, located in the body of the sphenoid bone and communicating with the highest meatus of the nasal cavity on the same side[MESH]. The sphenoidal sinuses (or sphenoid) contained within the body of the sphenoid vary in size and shape; owing to the lateral displacement of the intervening septum they are rarely symmetrical. The following are their average measurements: vertical height, 2.2 cm. ; transverse breadth, 2 cm. ; antero-posterior depth, 2.2 cm. [WP,unvetted].
UBERON:0001724.label: sphenoidal sinus

HP:0011767.definition: A functional abnormality of the parathyroid gland.
HP:0011767.label: Abnormality of the parathyroid physiology

UBERON:0001728.definition: the section of the pharynx that lies above the soft palate
UBERON:0001728.label: nasopharynx

HP:0030791.definition: A structural anomaly of the jaw, the bony structure of the mouth that consists of the mandible and the maxilla.
HP:0030791.label: Abnormal jaw morphology

UBERON:0004708.definition: An appendage that is part of an appendage girdle complex.
UBERON:0004708.label: paired limb/fin

HP:0011002.definition: Abnormally increased formation of dense trabecular bone tissue. Despite the increased density of bone tissue, osteopetrotic bones tend to be more fracture-prone than normal.
HP:0011002.label: Osteopetrosis

HP:0001789.definition: The abnormal accumulation of fluid in two or more fetal compartments, including ascites, pleural effusion, pericardial effusion, and skin edema.
HP:0001789.label: Hydrops fetalis

HP:0011001.definition: An abnormal increase of bone mineral density, that is, of the amount of matter per cubic centimeter of bones which is often refered to as osteosclerosis. Osteosclerosis can be detected on radiological examination as an increased whiteness (density) of affected bones.
HP:0011001.label: Increased bone mineral density

UBERON:0001295.definition: the glandular mucous membrane lining of the uterine cavity that is hormonally responsive during the estrous/menstrual cycle and during pregnancy
UBERON:0001295.label: endometrium

UBERON:0001297.definition: Outer serosa layer of the uterus.
UBERON:0001297.label: serosa of uterus

UBERON:0001296.definition: the smooth muscle coat of the uterus, which forms the main mass of the organ and surrounds and supports the endometrium
UBERON:0001296.label: myometrium

UBERON:0004704.definition: A depression or hollow in a bone[WP].
UBERON:0004704.label: bone fossa

UBERON:0000033.definition: The head is the anterior-most division of the body [GO].
UBERON:0000033.label: head

UBERON:0002530.definition: an organ that functions as a secretory or excretory organ
UBERON:0002530.label: gland

HP:0000252.definition: Occipito-frontal (head) circumference (OFC) less than -3 standard deviations compared to appropriate, age matched, normal standards (Ross JJ, Frias JL 1977, PMID:9683597). Alternatively, decreased size of the cranium.
HP:0000252.label: Microcephaly

UBERON:0011215.definition: A multi cell part structure that is part of a central nervous system.
UBERON:0011215.label: central nervous system cell part cluster

HP:0002143.definition: An abnormality of the spinal cord (myelon).
HP:0002143.label: Abnormality of the spinal cord

UBERON:0007650.definition: The junction between the esophagus and the stomach epithelium
UBERON:0007650.label: esophagogastric junction

UBERON:0011216.definition: A subdivision of an anatomical system.
UBERON:0011216.label: organ system subdivision

UBERON:0002349.definition: the middle layer of the heart, comprised mainly of striated cardiac muscle fibers
UBERON:0002349.label: myocardium

HP:0009804.definition: The presence of a reduced number of teeth as in Hypodontia or as in Anodontia.
HP:0009804.label: Reduced number of teeth

UBERON:0008883.definition: Bone tissue that is an unmineralized bone matrix deposited by osteoblasts prior to the mineralization of bone tissue.
UBERON:0008883.label: osteoid

UBERON:0016410.definition: A breast that is part of a male organism.
UBERON:0016410.label: male breast

UBERON:0001708.definition: Subdivision of skeleton which includes upper and lower jaw skeletons.
UBERON:0001708.label: jaw skeleton

UBERON:0001052.definition: the terminal portion of the intestinal tube, terminating with the anus
UBERON:0001052.label: rectum

UBERON:0000025.definition: Any hollow cylindrical anatomical structure containing a lumen through which substances are transported.
UBERON:0000025.label: tube

UBERON:0000458.definition: The region of the opening of the uterine cervix into the uterine cavity.
UBERON:0000458.label: endocervix

UBERON:0013685.definition: Anatomical space that is an opening in a bone of the skull.
UBERON:0013685.label: foramen of skull

HP:0005387.definition: A group of phenotypically heterogeneous genetic disorders characterized by profound deficiencies of T- and B-cell function, which predispose the patients to both infectious and noninfectious complications.
HP:0005387.label: Combined immunodeficiency

UBERON:0001156.definition: Section of colon which is distal to the cecum and proximal to the transversecolon.[FMA,modified]
UBERON:0001156.label: ascending colon

UBERON:0001157.definition: The proximal-distal subdivision of colon that runs transversely across the upper part of the abdomen, from the right to the left colic flexure. Continuous with the descending colon[BTO,modified].
UBERON:0001157.label: transverse colon

UBERON:0001154.definition: A blind-ended tube connected to the cecum, from which it develops embryologically[WP].
UBERON:0001154.label: vermiform appendix

UBERON:0001155.definition: Last portion of the large intestine before it becomes the rectum.
UBERON:0001155.label: colon

UBERON:0001158.definition: The portion of the colon between the left colic flexure and the sigmoid colon at the pelvic brim; the portion of the descending colon lying in the left iliac fossa is sometimes called the iliac colon.
UBERON:0001158.label: descending colon

HP:0010468.definition: Absence or underdevelopment of the testes.
HP:0010468.label: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the testes

UBERON:0002030.definition: Projection of skin containing the outlets for 15-20 lactiferous ducts arranged cylindrically around the tip.
UBERON:0002030.label: nipple

UBERON:0001650.definition: Cranial nerve that innervates the muscles of the tongue.
UBERON:0001650.label: hypoglossal nerve

UBERON:0003134.definition: A female organ involved in reproduction
UBERON:0003134.label: female reproductive organ

UBERON:0003135.definition: A male organ involved in reproduction
UBERON:0003135.label: male reproductive organ

UBERON:0002405.definition: Anatomical system that protects the body from foreign substances, cells, and tissues by producing the immune response and that includes especially the thymus, spleen, lymphoid tissue, lymphocytes including the B cells and T cells, and antibodies.
UBERON:0002405.label: immune system

UBERON:0002407.definition: The combination of pericardial sac (a double-walled sac containing the heart and the roots of the great vessels) plus fibrous pericardium.
UBERON:0002407.label: pericardium

UBERON:0002368.definition: Endocrine glands are glands of the endocrine system that secrete their products directly into the circulatory system rather than through a duct.[WP, modified].
UBERON:0002368.label: endocrine gland

HP:0001252.definition: Muscular hypotonia is an abnormally low muscle tone (the amount of tension or resistance to movement in a muscle), often involving reduced muscle strength. Hypotonia is characterized by a diminished resistance to passive stretching.
HP:0001252.label: Muscular hypotonia

HP:0001250.definition: Seizures are an intermittent abnormality of the central nervous system due to a sudden, excessive, disorderly discharge of cerebral neurons and characterized clinically by some combination of disturbance of sensation, loss of consciousness, impairment of psychic function, or convulsive movements. The term epilepsy is used to describe chronic, recurrent seizures.
HP:0001250.label: Seizures

HP:0030956.definition: An anomaly of the electrical conduction physiology of the heart.
HP:0030956.label: Abnormality of cardiovascular system electrophysiology

UBERON:0002036.definition: Muscle tissue that contains fibers that are divided by transverse bands into striations.
UBERON:0002036.label: striated muscle tissue

UBERON:0010185.definition: A structure formed from the primary sex cords in females, counterpart of the rete testis in males.
UBERON:0010185.label: rete ovarii

UBERON:0000094.definition: Nonparenchymatous organ that primarily consists of dense connective tissue organized into a sheet which interconnects two or more organs, separates two or more body spaces from one another, or surrounds an organ or body part. Examples: interosseous membrane of forearm, obturator membrane, tympanic membrane, fibrous pericardium, fascia lata, dura mater. [FMA]
UBERON:0000094.label: membrane organ

UBERON:0001159.definition: The part of the large intestine that is closest to the rectum and anus. It forms a loop that averages about 40 cm. in length, and normally lies within the pelvis, but on account of its freedom of movement it is liable to be displaced into the abdominal cavity.
UBERON:0001159.label: sigmoid colon

UBERON:0000093.definition: A depression or fissure in the surface of an organ.
UBERON:0000093.label: sulcus

HP:0000079.definition: An abnormality of the urinary system.
HP:0000079.label: Abnormality of the urinary system

HP:0000078.definition: An abnormality of the genital system.
HP:0000078.label: Abnormality of the genital system

UBERON:0003885.definition: A mesentery that is part of a uterus [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0003885.label: mesometrium

HP:0030680.definition: Any structural anomaly of the heart and great vessels.
HP:0030680.label: Abnormality of cardiovascular system morphology

HP:0010461.definition: Abnormality of the male genital system.
HP:0010461.label: Abnormality of the male genitalia

UBERON:0001162.definition: The part of the stomach attached to the esophagus. The cardia begins immediately distal to the z-line of the gastroeosphageal junction, where the squamous epithelium of the esophagus gives way to the columnar epithelium of the gastrointestinal tract[WP]
UBERON:0001162.label: cardia of stomach

UBERON:0003297.definition: A gland that is part of a integumental system [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0003297.label: gland of integumental system

UBERON:0003296.definition: Any gland that is part of the diencephalon. Examples: pineal gland, neurohypophysis.
UBERON:0003296.label: gland of diencephalon

UBERON:0001032.definition: Anatomical system that overlaps the nervous system and is responsible for receiving and processing sensory information.
UBERON:0001032.label: sensory system

UBERON:0012303.definition: The slit-like opening of either ureter into the bladder; normally, the two ureteral orifices are placed at the posterolateral angles of the urinary bladder trigone while the internal urethral orifice is placed at its anteroinferior angle (apex); wide gaping usually indicates vesicoureteral reflux
UBERON:0012303.label: ureteral orifice

UBERON:0003292.definition: A meninx that is part of a spinal cord [Automatically generated definition].
UBERON:0003292.label: meninx of spinal cord

UBERON:0001037.definition: A filament, mostly protein, that grows from follicles found in the dermis[WP].
UBERON:0001037.label: strand of hair

UBERON:0001677.definition: An unpaired bone situated at the base of the skull in front of the temporal bone and basilar part of the occipital bone. The sphenoid bone is one of the seven bones that articulate to form the orbit. Its shape somewhat resembles that of a butterfly or bat with its wings extended.
UBERON:0001677.label: sphenoid bone

UBERON:0004742.definition: The dentary is a dermal bone that forms the antero-lateral part of the lower jaw in fishes and amphibians, extending to the whole lower jaw in mammals[VHOG,modified].
UBERON:0004742.label: dentary

HP:0010668.definition: An abnormality of the zygomatic bone.
HP:0010668.label: Abnormality of the zygomatic bone

UBERON:0003729.definition: A mucous membrane that lines the mouth.
UBERON:0003729.label: mouth mucosa

HP:0000940.definition: An abnormality of the structure or form of the diaphysis, i.e., of the main or mid-section (shaft) of a long bone.
HP:0000940.label: Abnormal diaphysis morphology

UBERON:0005431.definition: A blood vessel that supplies the anterior portion of the spinal cord. It arises from branches of the vertebral arteries and is supplied by the anterior segmental medullary arteries, including the artery of Adamkiewicz, and courses along the anterior aspect of the spinal cord.
UBERON:0005431.label: anterior spinal artery

UBERON:0001255.definition: distensible musculomembranous organ situated in the anterior part of the pelvic cavity in which urine collects before excretion[MP].
UBERON:0001255.label: urinary bladder

UBERON:0000915.definition: Subdivision of trunk that lies between the head and the abdomen.
UBERON:0000915.label: thoracic segment of trunk

UBERON:0003722.definition: The compartment containing the anterior extremities and half the inferior surface of the temporal lobes (TEMPORAL LOBE) of the cerebral hemispheres. Lying posterior and inferior to the anterior cranial fossa (CRANIAL FOSSA, ANTERIOR), it is formed by part of the TEMPORAL BONE and SPHENOID BONE. It is separated from the posterior cranial fossa (CRANIAL FOSSA, POSTERIOR) by crests formed by the superior borders of the petrous parts of the temporal bones[MESH]. The middle fossa, deeper than the anterior cranial fossa, is narrow medially and widens laterally to the sides of the skull. It is separated from the posterior fossa by the clivus and the petrous crest. It is bounded in front by the posterior margins of the lesser wings of the sphenoid bone, the anterior clinoid processes, and the ridge forming the anterior margin of the chiasmatic groove; behind, by the superior angles of the petrous portions of the temporal bones and the dorsum sellC&; laterally by the temporal squamC&, sphenoidal angles of the parietals, and greater wings of the sphenoid. It is traversed by the squamosal, sphenoparietal, sphenosquamosal, and sphenopetrosal sutures[WP].
UBERON:0003722.label: middle cranial fossa

HP:0008905.definition: Disproportionate shortening of the proximal segment of limbs (i.e. the femur and humerus).
HP:0008905.label: Rhizomelia

HP:0100324.definition: A chronic autoimmune phenomenon characterized by fibrosis (or hardening) and vascular alterations of the skin.
HP:0100324.label: Scleroderma

UBERON:0010363.definition: A skeletal element that has the potential to participate in endochondral ossification, and may participate in intramembranous ossification.
UBERON:0010363.label: endochondral element

UBERON:0011374.definition: A retractable double-layered fold of skin and mucous membrane that covers the glans penis or clitoris. Glands may also be present.
UBERON:0011374.label: prepuce

HP:0000556.definition: Retinal dystrophy is an abnormality of the retina associated with a hereditary process. Retinal dystrophies are defined by their predominantly monogenic inheritance and they are frequently associated with loss or dysfunction of photoreceptor cells as a primary or secondary event.
HP:0000556.label: Retinal dystrophy

UBERON:0002101.definition: A paired appendage that is evolved from a paired fin. The extent of this structure includes autopod, stylopod and zeugopod regions when present, but excludes the girdle and its parts.
UBERON:0002101.label: limb

UBERON:0001323.definition: The tibial nerve is a branch of the sciatic nerve. The tibial nerve passes through the popliteal fossa to pass below the arch of soleus. In the popliteal fossa the nerve gives off branches to gastrocnemius, popliteus, soleus and plantaris muscles, an articular branch to the knee joint, and a cutaneous branch that will become the sural nerve. The sural nerve is joined by fibres from the common peroneal nerve and runs down the calf to supply the lateral side of the foot. Below the soleus muscle the nerve lies close to the tibia and supplies the tibialis posterior, the flexor digitorum longus and the flexor hallucis longus. The nerve passes into the foot running posterior to the medial malleolus. Here it is bound down by the flexor retinaculum in company with the posterior tibial artery. [WP,unvetted].

UBERON:0001322.definition: A large nerve that supplies nearly the whole of the skin of the leg, the muscles of the back of the thigh, and those of the leg and foot. It begins in the lower back and runs through the buttock and down the lower limb.

HP:0100021.definition: Cerebral palsy describes a group of permanent disorders of the development of movement and posture, causing activity limitation, that are attributed to nonprogressive disturbances that occurred in the developing fetal or infant brain. The motor disorders of cerebral palsy are often accompanied by disturbances of sensation, perception, cognition, communication, and behaviour, by epilepsy, and by secondary musculoskeletal problems.
HP:0100021.label: Cerebral palsy

UBERON:0001043.definition: Tube that connects the pharynx to the stomach. In mammals, the oesophagus connects the buccal cavity with the stomach. The stratified squamous non-keratinised epithelium lining the buccal cavity is continued through the pharynx down into the oesophagus. The lowest part of the oesophagus (ca. 2 cm) is lined with gastric mucosa and covered by peritoneum. The main body of the oesophagus is lined with small, simple mucous glands. Each gland opens into the lumen by a long duct which pierces the muscularis mucosae (Wilson and Washington, 1989). A sphincter is situated at the point where the oesophagus enters the stomach to prevent gastro-oesophageal reflux, i.e. to prevent acidic gastric contents from reaching stratified epithelia of the oesophagus, where they can cause inflammation and irritation (Wilson and Washington, 1989; Brown et al., 1993).
UBERON:0001043.label: esophagus

UBERON:0001756.label: middle ear

UBERON:0001757.definition: The part of the ear that projects from the head, connecting to the external acoustic meatus.

UBERON:0002360.definition: Membrane organ that surrounds the brain and the spinal cord.

UBERON:0034933.definition: Any organ component layer that consists of smooth muscle tissue.

UBERON:0002364.definition: A thin membrane that separates the external ear from the middle ear, consisting of two epithelia (one part of the the external accoustic meatus epithelium, the other part of the tympanic cavity epithelium) with a fibrous layer between them. UBERON:0001813.definition: an intermingling of fiber fascicles from adjacent spinal nerves to form a network.

UBERON:0002285.label: telencephalic ventricle

UBERON:3000961.definition: Structures of the dermis, epidermis, glands and pigment cells recognizable on the external surfaces of the integument.

UBERON:0013630.definition: Short bones are designated as those bones that are as wide as they are long. Their primary function is to provide support and stability with little to no movement. They are one of five types of bones: long, short, flat, irregular and sesamoid. Examples of these bones include the tarsals in the foot and the carpals in the hand.
UBERON:0013630.label: short bone

UBERON:0003687.definition: In anatomy, in the occipital bone, the foramen magnum is one of the several oval or circular apertures in the base of the skull, through which the medulla oblongata (an extension of the spinal cord) enters and exits the skull vault. Apart from the transmission of the medulla oblongata and its membranes, the foramen magnum transmits the Spinal Accessory nerve, vertebral arteries, the anterior and posterior spinal arteries, the membrana tectoria and alar ligaments. [WP,unvetted].
UBERON:0003687.label: foramen magnum

HP:0001928.definition: An abnormality of the process of blood coagulation. That is, altered ability or inability of the blood to clot.
HP:0001928.label: Abnormality of coagulation

UBERON:0003889.definition: Initial section of the oviduct through which the ova pass from the ovary to the uterus
UBERON:0003889.label: fallopian tube

UBERON:0003914.definition: Epithelial tubes transport gases, liquids and cells from one site to another and form the basic structure of many organs and tissues, with tube shape and organization varying from the single-celled excretory organ in Caenorhabditis elegans to the branching trees of the mammalian kidney and insect tracheal system.
UBERON:0003914.label: epithelial tube

UBERON:0000159.definition: The terminal part of the large intestine, continuous proximally with the rectum and distally terminates with the anus.

UBERON:0034713.label: cranial neuron projection bundle
